(5'') 27 ME ina AN-e ZAL IGI', '', 791, '(4'') [In Cancer] (5’) it (Jupiter) remains invisible in heaven for 27 days, (then) it appears.', 'BM 34757', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon?', 'ca. 350-100 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2016, Ancient Babylonian astronomers calculated Jupiters position from the area under a time-velocity graph, Science, 351, 482-484', 'http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.aad8085', 'X4''-5''', 988, '', 'Alternatively ZAL = nasāḫu, to pass (said of time), may apply here.');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (433, '[GE₆ 19] DIR AN ZA ULU₃ GIN ina ZALAG₂ sin ar₂ MAŠ.MAŠ ar₂ 1 KUŠ₃ sin 5 KUŠ₃ ana ULU₃ SIG', '', 403, '[Night of (day) 19,] clouds were in the sky, the south wind blew; last part of the night, Sin was 1 cubit behind the rear twin, Sin being 5 cubits low to the south.', 'BM 35015+ (ADRT II No. -164B)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '165 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'obv. 7''', 541, '494-495', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (344, '[DIŠ mul.giš.APIN d.En-lil2 a-li]k pa-ni MUL.MEŠ šu-ut d.En-lil2', '', 325, '[¶ The Plough, Enlil, who go]es in front of the stars of Enlil.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 1', 439, '29', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (900, '⸢10⸣ LA₂-is-ma u₃ IGI e-lat 6 ME ZAL ša₂ MU', '', 791, 'It (Jupiter) recedes by 10 and, furthermore, the (first) appearance is, in addition, delayed by 6 days per year.', 'BM 34081+ (BMAPT No. 18)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 250-50 BCE', 'M. Ossendrijver, 2017, New results on a Babylonian scheme for Jupiter''s motion along the zodiac, Journal of Near Eastern Studies 76, 231–247', 'http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.aad8085', 'obv. i 3''', 987, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (420, 'iti.GAN 2 mul2.Ṣal-bat-a-nu 1.10 mul2.GIR2.TAB 35 mul2.[LU]GAL', '', 390, 'Month IX: 2 Mars, 1,10 ''The Scorpion'', 35 ''The [Ki]ng''.', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 9', 529, '126', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2284, 'hinc imitata nitent cursumque habitumque sagittae
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (660, '(14) bi-rit IGI ana IGI GIŠ.GIŠ.ḪI-ma
(15) 3.30.39.4.20 KI-šu₂ TAB-ma ME.MEŠ E-bi', '', 591, '(14) The distance from appearance to appearance you compute, and (15) 3;30,39,4,20 you add to it, and you predict the ‘days’.', 'AO 6477 (BMAPT No. 42)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 250-150 BCE', 'Ossendrijver 2012 No. 42', '', 'obv. 14-15', 777, '312-313', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (410, 'GE₆ 8 SAG GE₆ sin ina IGI MUL₂ IGI ša₂ še-pit MAŠ.MAŠ 1 1/2 KUŠ₃', '', 382, 'Night of the 8th, beginning of the night, Sin was 1 1/2 cubits in front of the front star of the twins'' feet.', 'BM 46229 (ADRT I No. -346)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '347 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 2', 519, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (386, '', 'ỉ swḥ n tꜣ p.t rsy.t ỉ msḫṱ n tꜣ p.t | mḥṱ.t', 363, 'Oh, Orion of the southern sky, oh Ursa Major of the |northern | sky ...', 'P.Rhind I', 'religious text', 'Thebes', '1st cent. BCE', 'G. Moller, 1913, Die beiden Totenpapyrus Rhind des Museum su Edinburg (Leipzig)', '', 'x 8-9d', 496, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1927, 'Extra partes Sagittarii oritur Falcis Lupus Aquarius minor et Ara.', '', 1713, 'Outside the degrees of Sagittarius rises the Sickle, the Wolf, the Small Waterbearer and the Altar.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '8.29.13', 2016, '2.351', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (184, '¶ ina iti.ŠU BAR2 GAL UŠ₂-ma DUMU-šú AŠ.TE DAB ŠE.GIŠ.I₃ ⸢u?⸣ […]', '', 188, 'If in Dûzu the harvest a great king will die and his son will take the throne, Sesame [...]', 'Sm.1281 + Rm-II.132', 'celestial divination: enūma anu enlil', 'Nineveh', '', 'Gehlken, E. 2008. Die Adad-Tafeln der Omenserie Enuma Anu Enlil; T. 2: die ersten beiden Donnertafeln (EAE 42 und EAE 43). Zeitschrift für Orient-Archäologie, 1, 256-314.', '', '4''', 272, '266', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (366, 'ME u GI₆ ana DU₃-ka 18 MU.MEŠ ana ⸢EGIR-ka GUR⸣', '', 321, '(In order) for you to compute ME and GI₆ you turn back 18 years.', 'BM 42282+', 'goal year procedure', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Brack-Bernsen L., Hunger H., 2008, "BM 42282+42294 and the Goal-Year Method." SCIAMVS 9, 3-23.', '', 'rev. 19''', 470, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (486, 'GI₆ 10 SAG GI₆ sin ar₂ MUL₂ ar₂ ša₂ SUḪUR.MAŠ₂ 1 1/2 KUŠ₃', '', 444, 'Night of the 10th, beginning of the night, the moon was 1 1/2 cubits behind the rear star of the goat-fish.', 'BM 37231 (ADRT I No. -333)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '334 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 11''', 597, '166-167', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (411, '(28) GE₆ 23 USAN AN e MUL₂ ar₂ (29) [ša₂ še]-⸢pit⸣ MAŠ.MAŠ 20 SI', '', 383, 'Night of the 23rd, first part of the night, Mars was 20 fingers above the rear star of the twins'' feet.', 'BM 46229 (ADRT I No. -346)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '347 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 28-29', 520, '150-151', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (434, '[GE₆ 19] DIR AN ZA ULU₃ GIN ina ZALAG₂ sin ar₂ MAŠ.MAŠ ar₂ 1 KUŠ₃ sin 5 KUŠ₃ ana ULU₃ SIG', '', 403, '[Night of (day) 19,] clouds were in the sky, the south wind blew; last part of the night, Sin was 1 cubit behind the rear twin, Sin being 5 cubits low to the south.', 'BM 35015+ (ADRT II No. -164B)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '165 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'obv. 7''', 542, '494-495', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (600, 'Ἥλιος, Ἀφροδίτη Ὑδροχόῳ, Σελήνη, Ζεὺς Τοξότῃ, Κρόνος Λέοντι, Ἑρμῆς Αἰγοκέρωτι, Ἄρης, ὡροσκόπος Ζυγῷ.', '', 539, 'The Sun, Venus (were) in Aquarius; the Moon, Jupiter in Sagittarius; Saturn in Leo; Mercury in Capricorn; Mars, the Ascendant in Libra.', 'Vettius Valens', 'horoscope', '', '2nd century CE', '(GH L 122,I,22)', '', '5.6.112', 715, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1227, 'solus in cardinibus geniturae fuerit inventus vel in cataforis vel in anaforis eorum', '', 1101, 'alone on an angle or on the anafora or catafora of an angle [= the sign before or after]', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '3.5.5', 1320, '1.128', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (667, 'mul.tul-tu4 d.A-nu-ni-tu4', '', 597, 'Maggot-star : Anunitu.', 'AO 8196', 'star list', '?', '700-500 BCE', 'Koch-Westenholz, U., 1995. Mesopotamian Astrology. An Introduction to Babylonian and Assyrian Celestial Divination. Copenhagen: Museum Tusculanum Press.', '', 'iii 27', 784, '194', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (345, '[iti.G]U4 3.40 MUL2.MUL2 1.40 mul2.Dil-bat 50 mul2.APIN', '', 325, '[Mon]th 2: 3,40 ''The Stars'', 1,40 Venus, 50 ''The Plough''', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 2', 439, '126', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (563, 'τὸν δὲ ὡρονόμον ὡροσκόπον προσδεῖ δι’ ὅλην τὴν [ἀν]αλογίαν ἐκ τοῦ ἀναφορικοῦ πρὸς κλεψύδραν· ἐκπείπτει ἐν Καρκίνωι περὶ μοιρῶν κεʹ', '', 508, 'It is also necessary (to calculate) the hour-apportioning Ascendant from the (table) of rising-times in complete proportion by water-clock: the result is in Cancer, about 25 degrees.', 'P.Lond. 98', 'horoscope', 'Egypt', '95 CE', 'GH 95', '', '59–61', 677, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (901, '(3) ⸢ina 20⸣ NINDA
(4) šal-šu₂ ḪAB-rat sin al
(5) MURUB₄ KASKAL.2 NIM', '', 792, '(3) In 20 nindanu , (4) a third of the disk, Sin ascends above (5) the middle of the path.', 'BM 35739 (BMAPT No. 99)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 400-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'side X i'' 3-5', 989, '513', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2311, 'Saturni, Iovis et Martis Solisque, sub illis
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2379, 'quin etiam Arcitenens, qui te, Capricorne, sub ipso
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (282, '', 'rꜥ-ḫꜥ ỉḫy.t | rꜥ-ḥtp ỉsw | šy p.t pꜣ gnḥḏ | šy dwꜣ.t pꜣ ḥr-ꜥnḫ ḥr-pꜣ-kꜣ | pꜣ swšp n mtr [nꜣ] ḥtr.w | pꜣ swšp ỉꜣbṱ nꜣ (?) tbt.w| pꜣ swšp ỉmnṱ tꜣ rpy.t | twr n ỉmnṱ pꜣ ỉsw | twr n ỉꜣbṱ pꜣ mw pꜣ mꜣy', 281, 'Ascendant: Libra | Descendant: Aries | Lake of the Sky: Cancer | Lake of the Netherworld: Capricorn |the middle swšp: Gemini | the eastern swšp: pisces | the western swšp: Virgo | western twr: Aries | eastern twr: Aquarius and Leo.', 'O.Neugeb. 3', 'horoscope', 'Thebes', '1st cent. CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 116-117', '', '4-12', 384, '116-117', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (275, 'MUL4 u ṣal-lum-mu-[u2 ...]', '', 276, 'A star or a come[t ...]', 'BM 36353+36647', 'astrology', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Schreiber, M. 2018. Astrologische Wettervorhersagen und Kometenbeobachtungen. In: Grenzüberschreitungen. Studien zur Kulturgeschichte des Alten Orients (Fs. H. Neumann), eds. Kristin Kleber, Georg Neumann, and Susanne Paulus. Zaphon: Münster: 739-756.', '', 'rev. v 11''', 378, '743', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (481, '(30) GE₆ 2 ina ZALAG₂ dele-bat SIG GIR₃ ar₂ ša₂ A (31) ⸢2⸣ SI DIM₄', '', 440, '(30) Night of (day) 2, last part of the night, Venus came near 2 fingers below the rear foot of the lion.', 'BM 35070+ (ADRT III No. -132B)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '133 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1996. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. III. Diaries from 164 B.C. to 61 B.C. Vienna, Austria: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'obv. 30-31', 595, '214-215', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2587, '†σίν· τὴν σελήνην. ββῶν†', '', 535, 'Sin: the Moon. Babylonians.', 'Hesychius', 'lexicon', 'Alexandria', '4th-6th century CE', 'Hesychius Alexandrinus. 2005. Hesychii Alexandrini Lexicon, Vol. 3 (Pi - Sigma), ed. P.A. Hansen. Berlin, New York: Walter de Gruyter.', 'https://doi.org/10.1515/9783110193800', 'σ 674', 711, '292', 'The manuscript contains σεμνήν instead of σελήνην.');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1604, 'ina ZALAG₂ ina ᵈUTU.E₃.A ṣal-⸢lum⸣-[mu-u₂ ...]', '', 276, 'Last part of the night, a com[et] in the east [...]', 'Rm 694+ (ADRT II No. -234A)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '235 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 3''', 378, '96-97', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (973, 'minuuntur autem etiam haec, si sic positum Solem malivolum sidus impediat.', '', 869, 'these things however are lessened if a malefic planet impedes the sun in that position', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '3.5.37', 1065, '1.141', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (958, 'cur non [...] ad occidentem transferat orientique restituat', '', 854, 'why it does not carry [...] over to the west and return it back to the east', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '1.0.5', 1046, '1.3', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (506, '[3]0 U4.MEŠ 1 DANNA šu-u2 2 ½ u4-mu a-na 1-en ḪA.LA ŠID-ma 12 UZU.MEŠ ḪA.LA ša2 mul2.lu2.ḪUN.GA2 ip-pal-ka', '', 463, '30 days are 1 bēru (= 30°); you count 2 1/2 days for one portion, and 12 ''limbs'', portion(s) of Aries, it gives you.', 'AO 6483 (TCL 6 14 = TU 14)', 'horoscopic astrology', 'Uruk', '250-150 BCE', 'Sachs, A., 1952. Babylonian Horoscopes, Journal of Cuneiform Studies 6: 49-75.', '', '10''-11''', 616, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1282, 'nam in nocturnis genituris initium ac dominium ipsa suscipit temporum, in diurnis vero genituris Sol;', '', 1139, 'for in night charts the beginning and rulership of time she [the Moon] possesses herself, in day charts, however, the Sun  does', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '4.1.8', 1375, '1.199', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (412, '(18) ⸢GE₆⸣ [6] (19) SAG GE₆ sin e MAŠ.MAŠ ša₂ SIPA 20 SI', '', 384, '(18) Ni[ght of (day) 6,] (19) beginning of the night, Sin was 20 fingers above the twins’ star of the shepherd.', 'BM 46229 (ADRT I No. -346)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '347 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 18-19', 521, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (85, '[EN.NUN ša₂ gi-ne2]-e ša2 TA BAR EN TIL DU6 MU 1 ME 50.KAM2 man LUGAL', '', 102, '[Diary] from month I to the end of month VII, year 150, king Antiochus', 'BM 34140', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '-161', 'Hunger & Sachs ADRT 1', '', 'l.e. 1', 143, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (487, 'GE₆ 27 ina ZALAG₂ sin e MUL₂-IGI-ša₂-ALLA-ša₂-SI 1 KUŠ₃ sin 1/2 KUŠ₃ ana ŠU₂ LAL', '', 445, 'Night of (day) 27, last part of the night, Sin was 1 cubit above the front star of the crab to the north, Sin being 1/2 cubit back to the west.', 'BM 43025+ (ADRT III No. -77A)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '78 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1996. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. III. Diaries from 164 B.C. to 61 B.C. Vienna, Austria: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 14', 598, '494-495', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (435, '(3) ša₂ GENNA 25.24.5 NIM ⸢2⸣[2.41.25 SIG] (4) 12 taš an-na-a [ša₂ ME.MEŠ]', '', 122, '(3) For Saturn: the ‘height’ is 25;24,5, [the ‘depth’ is 22;41,25], (4) the difference is (0);12; thus [for the ‘days’].', 'A 3418 (BMAPT No. 41)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 170-200 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 3-4', 238, '310', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (367, '(22) ina 5 DANNA si-man 5 UŠ (23) ᵈsin ana ᵈUTU.ŠU₂.A tu-šaḫ-ḫa-az', '', 347, '(22) In 5 bēru of time you let (23) Sin proceed 5 UŠ to the west.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. ii 22-23', 471, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (461, '¶ mul.dil-bat ina iti.Š[E i]ti.DIRI.ŠE d-30 mul.ŠU.PA', '', 425, 'When Venus in Month XII, intercalary month XII Sin ŠU.PA', 'K 42', 'celestial divination: enūma anu enlil', 'Nineveh', '', 'Reiner, E., Pingree, D. 1998. Babylonian Planetary Omens: Part Three.', '', 'rev. 1', 577, '194-195', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1928, 'In Pisce septentrionali oritur Cervus Lepus, in australi Cetus id est marina belua.', '', 1714, 'In the Northern Fish rise the Stag, the Hare, in the Southern [Fish rises] Cetus, i. e. the sea monster.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '8.30.12', 2017, '2.356', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (564, 'ἀνοικοδεσπότητος ἡ γένεσις διὰ τὸ ὑπὸ δύσιν ἐμπεπτωκέναι Ἀφροδίτην τὴν κυρίαν τῶν ὁρίων τῆς Σελήνης', '', 509, 'The nativity is without a house-master because Venus, the lord of the terms of the Moon, has fallen below the Descendant', 'Vettius Valens', 'horoscope', '', '2nd century CE', '(GH L 75)', '', '3.5.8', 678, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (436, '(5) ša₂ GENNA 14.4.42.30 LA₂ 11.14.2.⸢30⸣ [SIG] (6) 12 taš an-na-a KI.⸢MEŠ⸣', '', 122, '(5) For Saturn: the ‘height’ is 14;4,42,30, [the ‘depth’ is] 11;14,2, 30 , (6) the difference is (0);12; thus the positions.', 'A 3418 (BMAPT No. 41)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 170-200 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 5-6', 238, '310', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (507, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 ina ZAG-šu2 GUB-zu mul.ŠAḪ d.Da-mu', '', 464, '¶ The star which stands on its right: the Pig, Damu.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 29', 617, '35', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (23, '', 'ꜣbd-1 ꜣḫ.t tꜣ ḏlꜣ(.t)', 67, 'Thoth: Scorpio', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521', 'astronomical list', '', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '10', 70, '121', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (31, 'DIŠ 30 ina MUL.UR.G[U.LA AN.GE6 GAR-ma (…)]', '', 75, 'If the moon [is eclipsed] in Le[o] (…)', 'BM 36746+', 'zodiacal astrology: celestial divination', 'Babylon', 'ca. 400-300 BCE', 'Rochberg, Francesca. 1984. New evidence for the history of astrology. JNES 43: 115-140.', '', 'obv. 5‘', 84, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (427, 'Ἥλιος, Ζεὺς Αἰγοκέρωτι, Σελήνη, Κρόνος Λέοντι, Ἄρης Ἰχθύσιν, Ἀφροδίτη, ὡροσκόπος Σκορπίῳ, Ἑρμῆς Τοξότῃ. οἱ αἰτιατικοὶ τόποι εὑρέθησαν Ἰχθύσι καὶ Σκορπίῳ· ἐν δὲ Σκορπίῳ Ἀφροδίτη, ἐν Ἰχθύσιν Ἄρης.', '', 397, 'Sun, Jupiter in Capricorn; the Moon, Saturn in Leon; Mars in Pisces; Venus, the Ascendant in Scorpio; Mercury in Sagittarius. The causal places were found in Pisces and Scorpio, and in Scorpio, Venus, in Pisces, Mars.', 'Vettius Valens', 'horoscope', '', '2nd century CE', '(GH L 123,I)', '', '5.6.119–120', 535, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (368, '(21) 2 (22) A.RA₂ 2.30 5 DANNA u₄-me ša₂ NIM.A DU-ma', '', 348, '(21) 2 (22) you multiply by 2,30, (i.e.) 5 bēru, the time since sunrise (to New Moon), it is 5.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. ii 21-22', 473, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (252, '30 ME ina IGI-at ŠU₂-šu₂ ša₂ ME 5 ZI-ma ŠU₂', '', 258, '30 days before its setting it (Saturn) moves (0);5 per day, then it sets.', 'AO 6477 (BMAPT No. 42)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 250-150 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 4', 351, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (167, 'συμπαθεῖς εἰσιν οἱ κατ’ ἴσον ἀπέχοντες κατ’ ἐπιθεώρησιν ἀλλήλων σύμφωνοι· ἀσυμπαθεῖς δὲ οἱ κατὰ μηδένα τρόπον ἐπιθεωροῦντες ἀλλήλους· ὅπερ γίνεται ἐκ τῆς τῶν ἀσυνδέτων ζῳδίων ἀποστροφίας· ἔστιν δὲ ἀσύνδετα τὰ παρ’ ἑκάτερα καὶ τὰ διὰ ϛʹ καὶ ηʹ ζῳδίων ἀριθμούμενα', '', 173, 'Sympathetic (planets) are those that are an equal distance apart and harmonious in their aspect with each other, and unsympathetic are those that are not in any kind of aspect with each other, which results from the aversion of unconnected zodiac signs. Unconnected (zodiac signs) are those that are counted one after another and six and eight apart.', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 832, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (15, '[...] 17.30 MUL2 IGI', '', 60, '[...] (in) 17;30 Taurus it (Mars) will appear.', 'A 3429', 'mathematical astronomy: synodic table', 'Uruk', 'ca. 250-170 BCE', 'Neugebauer ACT No. 502', '', 'obv. 11', 53, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (13, 'ana ŠEG3 ILLU ina ŠA3 mul.KU6 mul.GU.LA u MUL.MUL', '', 60, 'For rain (and) flood: in the Fish, the Great One, and the Bristle', 'BM 47494', 'late astrology', 'Babylon?', '464-337 BCE', 'Hunger, H. 2004. Stars, Cities, and Predictions. Pp. 16–32 in Studies in the History of the Exact Sciences in Honour of David Pingree, eds. Charles Burnett, Jan Hogendijk, Kim Plofker and Michio Yano. Leiden: Brill.', '', 'obv. 28', 54, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (347, '[iti.S]IG4 4 mul2.SIPA.ZI.NA 1.50 mul2.ŠU.GI 55 mul2.A-nu-ni-tu2', '', 327, '[Mo]nth III: 4 ''The True Shepherd of Heaven'', 1,50 ''The Old Man'', 55 Anunitu.', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 3', 442, '126', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (264, 'iti.DU₆ ni-i-ru d.en-lil₂
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (165, 'συμπαθεῖς εἰσιν οἱ κατ’ ἴσον ἀπέχοντες κατ’ ἐπιθεώρησιν ἀλλήλων σύμφωνοι· ἀσυμπαθεῖς δὲ οἱ κατὰ μηδένα τρόπον ἐπιθεωροῦντες ἀλλήλους· ὅπερ γίνεται ἐκ τῆς τῶν ἀσυνδέτων ζῳδίων ἀποστροφίας· ἔστιν δὲ ἀσύνδετα τὰ παρ’ ἑκάτερα καὶ τὰ διὰ ϛʹ καὶ ηʹ ζῳδίων ἀριθμούμενα', '', 171, 'Sympathetic (planets) are those that are an equal distance apart and harmonious in their aspect with each other, and unsympathetic are those that are not in any kind of aspect with each other, which results from the aversion of unconnected zodiac signs. Unconnected (zodiac signs) are those that are counted one after another and six and eight apart.', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 248, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (491, '', '(rꜥ)-ḫꜥ mw 22 (rꜥ)-ḥtp mꜣy 22 (šy-n-tꜣ)-p.t ḏlꜣ.t 20 | (šy-n-tꜣ)-dwꜣ.t kꜣ 20 šꜣw tbt(.w) {30} sšr rpy.t 30 špšy.t | ḥr-ꜥnḫ 14 wrꜣ(.t) gnhd ⌈14⌉ ꜥnḫ pꜣ-nty-ꜣtḥ | mwt ḥtr(.w) ḥꜥ(.w) rpy.t (y)ꜥb(.t) tbt(.w)', 452, 'Ascendant: Aquarius 22°; Descendant: Leo 22°; (Lake of the) Sky: Scorpio 20° | (Lake of the) Netherworld: Taurus 20° (Lot of the) Daimon: Pisces {30}; (Lot of the) Evil Daimon: Virgo 30°; (Lot of) Fortune: | Capricorn 14°; (Lot of) Misfortune: Cancer ⌈14°⌉; (Lot of) Life: Sagittarius | (Lot of) Death: Gemini; (Lot of) Flesh: Virgo; (Lot of) Illness: Pisces.', 'ANAshm.Mus.D.O. 641', 'horoscope', 'Athribis', '48 BCE', 'A. Winkler, 2022, The First Zodiac Sign and the Daimon: The Advent of an Astrological Tradition and Seven Elaborate Horoscopes, Studien our Alt''ägyptischen Culture 51:  267-319', '', '9-12', 602, '302', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (437, '(3) ša₂ GENNA 25.24.5 NIM ⸢2⸣[2.41.25 SIG] (4) 12 taš an-na-a [ša₂ ME.MEŠ]', '', 123, '(3) For Saturn: the ‘height’ is 25;24,5, [the ‘depth’ is 22;41,25], (4) the difference is (0);12; thus [for the ‘days’].', 'A 3418 (BMAPT No. 41)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 170-200 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', '3-4', 239, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (462, '¶ ina iti.DIRI.ŠE.KIN.KU₅ BAL-e MAR.TU-i', '', 425, '¶ an intercalary Month XII (belongs to) the Amorite reign', 'VAT 9412+11279', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', 'Assur', '687 BC', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 19 ́', 577, '91', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2312, 'Ipse autem quantum convexo mundus Olympo
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (317, 'aš2-šu2 d.GU4.UD ina KI.MEŠ ša2 NITA u MUNUS KI 30 MUNUS U3.[TU]', '', 96, 'Because Mercury in the regions of either a male or a female (stands) with the Moon: a female will be bor[n].', 'BM 35402 (LBAT 1593)', 'horoscopic astrology', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd century BCE', 'Reiner, E. 2000. Early Zodiologia and Related Matters. In: Wisdom, Gods and Literature, Studies in Assyriology in Honour of W. G. Lambert, eds. Andrew R. George and I. L. Finkel. Winona Lake, Indiana: Eisenbauns: 421-427.', '', 'obv. 8''', 125, '422', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (470, 'ἡ δὲ θεὰ καὶ σελασφόρος Σελήνη (...) ἐπὶ τῆς ῥάχεως ἀναβιβάζουσα τοῦ Ταύρου', '', 433, 'The goddess, the light-bearing Moon (...) was ascending upon the backbone of the Bull (Taurus)', 'P.Lond. I 130', 'horoscope', '', '81 CE', '(GH 81)', '', '73–88', 586, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (250, '30 ME ina IGI-at ŠU₂-šu₂ ša₂ ME 5 ZI-ma ŠU₂', '', 252, '30 days before its setting it (Saturn) moves (0);5 per day, then it sets.', 'AO 6477 (BMAPT No. 42)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 250-150 BCE', 'Ossendrijver 2012 No. 42', '', 'rev. 4', 341, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (348, '[iti].ŠU 3.40 mul2.KAK.SI.SA2 2 mul2.UR.A 1 mul2.MUŠ', '', 328, '[Mo]nth IV: 3,40 ''The Arrow'', 2 ''The Lion'', 1 ''The Snake''.', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 5', 578, '126', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (166, 'συμπαθεῖς εἰσιν οἱ κατ’ ἴσον ἀπέχοντες κατ’ ἐπιθεώρησιν ἀλλήλων σύμφωνοι· ἀσυμπαθεῖς δὲ οἱ κατὰ μηδένα τρόπον ἐπιθεωροῦντες ἀλλήλους· ὅπερ γίνεται ἐκ τῆς τῶν ἀσυνδέτων ζῳδίων ἀποστροφίας· ἔστιν δὲ ἀσύνδετα τὰ παρ’ ἑκάτερα καὶ τὰ διὰ ϛʹ καὶ ηʹ ζῳδίων ἀριθμούμενα', '', 172, 'Sympathetic (planets) are those that are an equal distance apart and harmonious in their aspect with each other, and unsympathetic are those that are not in any kind of aspect with each other, which results from the aversion of unconnected zodiac signs. Unconnected (zodiac signs) are those that are counted one after another and six and eight apart.', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 5, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (413, '(31) ma-la ina 18-ka kun-nu u ṭe-pi KI-šu₂ la ṭe-pu-u₂ u₃ nis-ḫu TA ŠA₃ ZI-ma al-la ITI (32) ša₂ UGU-šu₂ LA₂-u₂ ana kun-nu E', '', 212, '(31) Whatever (month) in your (year) 18 (preceding it) is full, and to which there is no addition added, and a subtraction is subtracted from it, and which is (32) less than the month preceding it, you declare it as full.', 'AO 6455 (TU 11)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 200 BCE', 'Brack-Bernsen, Lis, and Hunger, Hermann. 2002. TU 11. A Collection of Rules for the Prediction of Lunar Phases and of Month Lengths. SCIAMVS 3: 3–90.', '', 'obv. 31-32', 297, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (549, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 ina IGI-šu2 GUB-zu mul.Ḫe2-gal2-a-a SUKAL d.Nin-lil2', '', 494, '¶ The star which stands in front of it: the Abundant One, the minister of Ninlil.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 13', 664, '32', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (185, '', 'sẖ ḥm-nṯr n spd.t ỉmy-r(ꜣ) mšꜥ n ỉꜥḥ wꜥb n p(ꜣ) 5 sbꜣ ꜥnḫ.w', 112, 'Written by the prophet of Sothis, overseer of the moon''s movement, and wrist of the five living stars.', 'Graf.Phil. 421', 'inscription', 'Philae', '3rd cent. CE', 'Griffith, F.Ll., Catalogue of the Demotic Graffiti of the Dodecaschoenus (Oxford, 1935 - 1937)', '', '14', 153, '26-31', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (262, '', 'pꜣ šy p.t pꜣ-nty-ꜣtḥ pꜣ šy dwꜣ.t ḥtr.w', 266, 'Lake of the sky: Sagittarius | Lake of the Netherworld: Gemini', 'O.Neugeb. 2', 'horoscope', 'Thebes', '1st cent.CE', 'O. Neugebauer, “Demotic Horoscopes”, JAOS 63 (1943), 115–127.', '', '6-7', 362, '116-117', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (771, '', '...] ỉrm nꜣ ḏmꜥ.w (n) [nꜣ wnm]-wnw.t r ḥꜣṱ (n) pr-ꜥꜣ twtw r-r=w ḏr=w', 688, '...] with the Books of the astronomers while the heart of pharaoh was content with them all.', 'P.Carlsberg XI 10', 'literary text', 'Tebtunis', '2nd Cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F. and K. Ryholt, 2019, Petese Interpreting Astrology by Imhotep for King Nechepsos. Copenhagen, 2019, 161-183.', '', '1-2', 881, '162', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (125, 'ἔστι δὲ ἐν αὐτῷ τὰ μέσα τοῦ Αἰγόκερω καὶ οἱ πόδες τοῦ Ὑδροχόου (...) τοῦ Σκορπίου τὸ κέντρον· εἶτα διὰ τοῦ Τοξότου πρὸς τὰ μέσα τοῦ Αἰγόκερω συνάπτει', '', 143, 'In it (sc. the Tropic of Capricorn) are the middle of Capricorn (the goat-horned one) and the feet of Aquarius (...) the stinger of Scorpio, and then it joins to the middle of Capricorn via Sagittarius', 'Eudoxus apud Hipparchus', 'astronomy', '', '4th century BCE', '', '', '1.2.20', 196, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1048, 'hos fines Graeci oria vocant', '', 938, 'These terms the Greeks call oria (boundaries)', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.6.1', 1142, '1.46', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (657, '(1) [NIM u SIG ša₂] ⸢MUL₂.BABBAR⸣ 2/3 KUŠ₃ e DUR MURUB₄ NIM
(2)  [2/3 KUŠ₃] SIG DUR MURUB₄ SIG
(3)  ki-i ina mul₂.GIR₂.TAB NIM ina zib.ME BUR₃
(4)  a-na 1 DANNA 8 u NIM u SIG', '', 589, '(1) [Height and depth of] Jupiter: 2/3 cubit above the middle band it is ‘high’, (2) [2/3 cubit] below the middle band it is ‘low’. (3) If it ‘high’ in Scorpio it is ‘low’ in Pisces. (4) For 1 bēru it ascends and descends 8 fingers.', 'BM 37266 (BMAPT No. 47)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 1-4', 774, '334', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (713, 'Ὁ τῶν ζῳδίων κύκλος διαιρεῖται εἰς μέρη ιβ᾽, καὶ καλεῖται κοινῶς μὲν ἕκαστον τῶν τμημάτων δωδεκατημόριον, ἰδίως δὲ ἀπὸ τῶν ἐμπεριεχομένων ἀστέρων, ὑφ᾽ ὧν καὶ διατυποῦται ἕκαστον αὐτῶν, ζῴδιον.', '', 586, 'The zodiac is divided in 12 parts, and each of the sections is named a ''twelfth part'' generally, but after the encompassing stars, through which each of them is also formed, a ''zodiac sign'' specifically.', 'Geminus', 'astronomy', '', '1st century BCE', 'Geminus. 1898. Γεμίνου Εἰσαγωγή εἰς τὰ Φαινόμενα, Gemini Elementa Astronomiae, ed. C.H.A. Manitius. Leipzig: B.G. Teubner.', 'http://www.wilbourhall.org/pdfs/GeminusElementaAstronomiae.pdf', '1.1', 771, '2', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (183, 'iti.ŠU mul.SIPA.ZI.AN.NA
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1785, 'I. et II. partes Cancri sunt in capite collocatae', '', 1587, 'degrees 1 and 2 of Cancer are located in the head', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '8.4.4', 1877, '2.289', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (732, '(2'') 17.46.40 taš-pil-tu₂ (3'')  ⸢ša₂ 18⸣ MU.MEŠ', '', 657, '(2'') (0);17,46,40, the difference (3’) for 18 years.', 'BM 36722 (BMAPT No. 82)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 2''-3''', 851, '470-471', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (761, '(27'') si-man qa-tu-u₂ ana DU₃-ka a-šar TAB KI si-man-ni-ka TAB a-šar LA₂-u₂ TA si-man-[ni-ka]
(28'') LA₂ ana si-man qa-tu-u₂ GAR', '', 678, '(27’) In order for you to ‘construct’ the final time (interval) (K): where it is additive you add it (C′ ) to your time (interval) (G + J), where it is subtractive you (28’) deduct it from [your] time (interval), you put it down as the final time (interval).', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. ii 27''-28''', 871, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (823, '(12) ki DIŠ.U₄ ša₂ NIM al-la BE u BAR.NUN DIRI-at₂ BE u BAR.NUN TA lib₃-bi [NI]M
(13) ana NA GAR-an', '', 742, '(12) If the DIS̆.U₄ of height exceeds the elongation and the ṣiliptu-coefficient you subtract the elongation and the ṣiliptu-coefficient from it, (13) you put it down as NA.', 'BM 35399 (BMAPT No. 61A)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 12-13', 931, '398-399', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (197, '⸢ina⸣ ⸢iti⸣KIN.2.KAM UD.8.KAM ina dUTU.E₃ IGI ŠA₂ KUR ŠA₂?-ab', '', 199, 'in the intercalary month VI, day 8, at sunset morning first the middle', 'K 2321', 'celestial divination: enūma anu enlil', 'Nineveh', '', 'Reiner, E., Pingree, D. (1975). Babylonian Planetary Omens: Part One. Enūma Anu Enlil Tablet 63: The Venus Tablet of Ammiṣaduqa. Undena.', '', 'r. 9''', 293, '29-62', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (526, 'μετὰ ἔτος ξαʹ μῆνας ιʹ φθάνει ἡ μοῖρα τοῦ ὡροσκόπου καὶ ἡ Σελήνη εἰς τὸ τετράγωνον τοῦ Κρόνου, ὅπερ καὶ οὐκ ἀναιρεῖ διὰ τὸ μαρτυρεῖν αὐτῷ τὴν Ἀφροδίτην ἐν τῷ δευτέρῳ', '', 480, 'After the 61st year, 10 months, the degree of the Ascendant and the Moon come into quartile with Saturn, which also does not destroy (end the life) because Venus is in aspect with it in the second (place).', 'CCAG VI', 'horoscope', '', '', '', '', 'p. 68 (GH L 76)', 643, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1019, 'Signa autem ipsa duodecim his nominibus nominantur: Aries, Taurus, Gemini, Cancer, Leo, Virgo, Libra, Scorpius, Sagittarius, Capricornus, Aquarius et Pisces.', '', 912, 'The twelve signs themselves are called by these names: Aries, Taurus, Gemini, Cancer, Leo, Virgo, Libra, Scorpio, Sagittarius, Capricorn, Aquarius, and Pisces.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.1.2', 1117, '1.41', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (601, 'Ἥλιος, Ἀφροδίτη Ὑδροχόῳ, Σελήνη, Ζεὺς Τοξότῃ, Κρόνος Λέοντι, Ἑρμῆς Αἰγοκέρωτι, Ἄρης, ὡροσκόπος Ζυγῷ.', '', 540, 'The Sun, Venus (were) in Aquarius; the Moon, Jupiter in Sagittarius; Saturn in Leo; Mercury in Capricorn; Mars, the Ascendant in Libra.', 'Vettius Valens', 'horoscope', '', '2nd century CE', '(GH L 122,I,22)', '', '5.6.112', 716, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (209, '', 'Sbk | pꜣy=f ḫꜥ ỉmnṱ 1513 | tꜣy=f rnp.t ꜥꜣ.t 480', 219, 'Mercury | its evening rising | 1514 | its great year 480', 'ANAShm.Mus.D.O. 483', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Egypt', '3rd cent. BCE to 3rd cent. CE', 'Ossendrijver, M. and A. Winkler, 2018. Chaldeans on the Nile: Two Egyptian Procedure Texts with Babylonian System A1 and A2 for Mercury, in Scaffolding of Our Thoughts: Essays on Assyriology and the History of Science in Honor of Fracesca Rochberg, eds. J. Crisostomo et al. (Leiden: Brill, 2018), 282-418', '', '1-3', 304, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (707, '', '[pꜣy-ms=w] r tꜣ wḥm mḥ-2.t (n) tꜣ ḏlꜥ ṯꜣy swsw 11 šꜥ swsw 20 r pꜣ ỉꜥḥ mtry r sšm', 631, '[He who was born] when the second stage of Scorpio, from 11 degrees to 20 degrees, while the moon was in agreement with the (decan) Seshm.', 'P.Lille', 'astrological compendium', 'Tebtunis', '2nd century CE', 'M. Chauveau, 1992, "Un traité d''astrologie en écriture démotique", Cahiers de Recherches de l''Institut de Papyrologie et d''Égyptologie de Lille 14, 101-105', '', 'vi, x+23', 829, '104', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (205, '[M]U ana MU ŠU₂ ša₂ ŠU₂ u KUR ša₂ NIM', '', 215, 'Year by year, western setting and eastern rising.', 'BM 36321 (BMAPT No. 5)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 4', 300, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (438, '[DIŠ MUL ša2 KI z]a-ri-i ša2 MAR.GID2.DA GUB-zu [m]ul.KA5.A d.Er3-ra gaš-ri DINGIR.MEŠ', '', 326, '¶ The star which stands in the shaft of the Wagon: the Fox, Erra, the strong one of the gods.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 16-17', 441, '33', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (550, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 EGIR-šu2 GUB-zu MUL BAL.TEŠ2.A SUKAL d.MUŠ2', '', 495, '¶ The star which stands behind it: the Star of Dignity, the minister of Tišpak.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 14', 665, '32', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1422, '28 1.4 ŠU2', '', 1092, '(day) 28, 1,4 (UŠ before) the setting (of the sun)', 'BM 34066+ (ACT No. 120)', 'mathematical astronomy: synodic table', 'Babylon', '2nd century BCE', 'Neugebauer, Otto, 1955, Astronomical Cuneiform Texts', '', 'obv. 4 col. M (= time of New Moon)', 1311, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (772, '', '[ṯꜣy pꜣ swsw] mḥ-12 twtw (n) s-ḥm.t nꜣw smḥ', 689, '[From the] 12th [degree], it means female zodiac signs to the left;', 'P.Carlsberg XI 10', 'literary text', 'Tebtunis', '2nd Cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F. and K. Ryholt, 2019, Petese Interpreting Astrology by Imhotep for King Nechepsos. Copenhagen, 2019, 161-183.', '', '12', 882, '165', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (509, 'igi ana igi ta 25 maš.maš en 30 gir2.tab 30 tab', '', 448, '(First) appearance to (first) appearance. From 25 Gem until 30 Sco you add 30.', 'BM 34081+ (BMAPT No. 18)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 250-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. i 8''', 619, '248', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (101, 'šu-qa u šup-lu ša₂ ᵈsin KIN.KIN-ma', '', 122, 'The ''height'' and ''depth'' of Sin you investigate, and (...)', 'BM 35325 (LBAT 1600)', 'astrology', 'Babylon', 'ca. 450-50 BCE', 'Sachs, Abraham, Strassmaier, Johann N.,  Pinches, Theophilus. G. (1955). Late Babylonian astronomical and related texts.', '', 'rev. 9''', 167, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1929, 'quaedam vero aversa esse ab horoscopo et quodam modo aliena, quae non inmerito pigra diximus', '', 1715, 'these we call averse [unaspected] to the ascendant and in some way alien, which we rightly call dull', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.23.1', 2018, '1.70', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (733, '(5) ša₂ GENNA 14.4.42.30 LA₂ 11.14.2.⸢30⸣ [SIG]
(6) 12 taš an-na-a KI.⸢MEŠ⸣', '', 657, '(5) For Saturn: the ‘height’ is 14;4,42,30, [the ‘depth’ is] 11;14,2, 30, (6) the difference is (0);12; thus the positions.', 'A 3418 (BMAPT No. 41)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 170-200 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 5-6', 851, '310', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (801, '', 'tꜣy=s rnp.t mḥ 19 rnp.t n ꜥb tꜣy n ḥꜣ.ṱ=s pḥ.ṱ=s ỉr=s nmy ỉ.ỉr-ḥr [...', 716, 'Her 19th year: It is a year of miasma at the beginning and the end. She will be a flaming star before [...', 'P.Carlsberg XI 22', 'celestial divination', 'Tebtunis', '1st to 2nd century CE', 'Quack, J.F, 2019, Prognose über Desaster-Jahre, in K. Ryholt and J.F. Quack, eds, Demotic Literary Texts from Tebtunis and Beyond; Copenhagen, 273-281.', '', '5', 908, '279', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (218, '', 'pꜣy=f ḥtp ỉꜣbṱ 1223 tꜣy=f rnp.t ꜥꜣ.t 388', 226, 'Its eastern setting 1223; its great year 388', 'ANAshm.D.O. 525+', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Egypt', '', 'Ossendrijver, M. and A. Winkler, 2018. Chaldeans on the Nile: Two Egyptian Procedure Texts with Babylonian System A1 and A2 for Mercury, in Scaffolding of Our Thoughts: Essays on Assyriology and the History of Science in Honor of Fracesca Rochberg, eds. J. Crisostomo et al. (Leiden: Brill, 2018), 282-418', '', '9', 312, '388', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (838, 'DUR d.SAG.ME.GAR u d.Dil-bat GUB.MEŠ-ma 30 IR3 GISKIM.BI ana KUR KUR2 SUM', '', 754, 'DUR — Jupiter and Venus are present and the moon is eclipsed: Its sign is given for the enemy land.', 'O 176 (TCL VI 13 = TU 13)', 'late astrology', 'Uruk', '250-150 BCE', 'Rochberg, F., 1987. TCL 6 13: Mixed Traditions in Late Babylonian Astrology, Zeitschrift für Assyriologie 77: 207-228.', '', 'rev. ii 1', 945, '214', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (147, 'συνεργοί εἰσιν οἱ συνοδεύοντες, ὑπουργοὶ δὲ οἱ συμβάλλοντες', '', 157, 'Collaborators are the (stars) that travel together (are in conjunction?), and assistants are those that meet each other (in adjacent signs?)', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 10, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (489, '', '(rꜥ)-ḫꜥ mw 22 (rꜥ)-ḥtp mꜣy 22 (šy-n-tꜣ)-p.t ḏlꜣ.t 20 | (šy-n-tꜣ)-dwꜣ.t kꜣ 20 šꜣw tbt(.w) {30} sšr rpy.t 30 špšy.t | ḥr-ꜥnḫ 14 wrꜣ(.t) gnhd ⌈14⌉ ꜥnḫ pꜣ-nty-ꜣtḥ | mwt ḥtr(.w) ḥꜥ(.w) rpy.t (y)ꜥb(.t) tbt(.w)', 450, 'Ascendant: Aquarius 22°; Descendant: Leo 22°; (Lake of the) Sky: Scorpio 20° | (Lake of the) Netherworld: Taurus 20° (Lot of the) Daimon: Pisces {30}; (Lot of the) Evil Daimon: Virgo 30°; (Lot of) Fortune: | Capricorn 14°; (Lot of) Misfortune: Cancer ⌈14°⌉; (Lot of) Life: Sagittarius | (Lot of) Death: Gemini; (Lot of) Flesh: Virgo; (Lot of) Illness: Pisces.', 'ANAshm.Mus.D.O. 641', 'horoscope', 'Athribis', '48 BCE', 'A. Winkler, 2022, The First Zodiac Sign and the Daimon: The Advent of an Astrological Tradition and Seven Elaborate Horoscopes, Studien our Alt''ägyptischen Culture 51:  267-319', '', '9-12', 600, '302', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (824, '(9)  KI sin u KI šamaš₂ ša₂ al-la 10 lu-maš DIRI GAM₀ 8 DU KI ⸢BAR⸣.NUN ša₂ NIM u SIG ⸢ša₂⸣-[šu₂]
(10)  ki TAB TAB ki LA₂ LA₂ ana muḫ-ḫi a-ḫa-miš₂ GAR.GAR-ma ½-šu₂-nu GIŠ-ma GAM₀ DIŠ.U₄ ša₂ [NIM] u S[IG]
(11)  ša₂ taš-kun DU', '', 742, '(9) (The amount) by which the position of Sin and the position of Šamaš exceed 10 (UŠ) of the zodiacal sign you multiply by (0;0),8. You add it with the corresponding ṣiliptu-coefficient for ‘height and depth’ if it is increasing, subtract if it is decreasing. You accumulate (them) together, you compute half of it, and you multiply it by the DIŠ.U₄ of height and depth which you had put down.', 'BM 35399 (BMAPT No. 61A)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 9-11', 932, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (688, '(3) [ana] na-bal-kat₂-tu₄ ša₂ 20 ⸢MU⸣.AN.NA.MEŠ ŠU₂ ša₂ ⸢ŠU₂⸣
(4)  ⸢u⸣ KUR ša₂ NIM TA 30 ⸢ḪUN⸣ EN 30 A 4.49.17 LA₂
(5)  TA 30 A EN 20.30.07.30 ALLA 4.34.15 LA₂
(6)  TA 20.37.30 ALLA EN 30 ḪUN 5.32.51.30 LA₂', '', 616, '(3) [For] the transgression of 20 years, western setting (4) and eastern rising. From 30 Aries until 30 Leo you subtract 4;49,17. (5) From 30 Leo until 20;30,07,30 (error for 20;37,30) Cancer you subtract 4;34,15. (6) From 20;37,30 Cancer until 30 Aries you subtract 5;32,51,30 (error for 5;42,51,30?).', 'BM 36321 (BMAPT No. 5)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. 3-6', 810, '214-215', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (176, 'ὡς ὁμορόησις λέγεται ὅταν ἐν τοῖς αὐτῶν ὁρίοις ἀστέρες ὦσιν ἢ κατὰ κόλλησιν ἢ κατὰ σχῆμα οἱονδήποτε ἀλλήλους ἐφορῶσιν ἐν ὁρίοις τοῦ αὐτοῦ ἀστέρος ὄντες· κενοδρομία δὲ ὅταν ἡ Σελήνη μηδενὶ συνάπτῃ μήτε ζῳδιακῶς μήτε μοιρικῶς μήτε κατὰ κόλλησιν μήτε κατὰ σχῆμα μήτε μὴν ἐντὸς λʹ μοιρῶν τῶν ἔγγιστα συναφὴν ἢ σύνοδον ποιεῖσθαι μέλλῃ· καὶ ὡς κακοῖ τὸ σχῆμα τὴν γένεσιν.', '', 181, '(Antiochus says) that it is called “neighboring” whenever planets are in their terms, or are in attachment or in aspect with each other in any configuration in the terms of the same planet. “Running empty” is whenever the Moon is not in contact with any (planet), neither with respect to zodiac signs nor with respect to degrees nor in attachment(?) nor in configuration nor even about to make a union or conjunction within the next 30 degrees, and (Antiochus says) that this configuration oppresses the nativity.', 'Antiochus, Fragments', 'astrological treatise', 'Athens', '1st cent. BCE/1st cent. CE', 'CCAG VIII.3', '', '', 259, '114', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (860, 'Φαρμ / α ιε λα / ϛ ιε ι / ια ιδ νζ / ιϛ ιδ λζ / κα ιδ ιε / κϛ ιγ νγ', '', 761, 'Pharm(outhi) / 1 15 31 / 6 15 10 / 11 14 56 / 16 14 37 / 21 14 15 / 26 13 53', 'P. Oxy. LXI 4211', 'mathematical astronomy: five-day almanac', 'Oxyrhynchus', 'after 307 CE', 'Jones, A. (ed.), 1999. Astronomical papyri from Oxyrhynchus (P. Oxy. 4133-4300a), Volumes I and II. Philadelphia: American Philosophical Society.', 'https://archive.org/details/astronomicalpapy0001jone', '8-14', 955, 'I: 225 + II: 312-313', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (155, '', '[twys nꜣ] ⌈twtwꜣ⌉ [n] tꜣ p.t | [pꜣ mꜣy]  tꜣ [r]py.t| [tꜣ] ỉḫy.t tꜣ [ḏ]lꜣ.t', 163, '[See, the] ⌈zodiac signs⌉ [of] the sky: | [Leo] - Virgo | Libra - Scorpio', 'P.Carlsberg 9', 'astronomy', 'Soknopaiou Nesos', 'Second cent. CE', 'Neugebauer, O. & Parker, R.A. EAT 3', '', '1.5-7', 231, '220-225', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1930, 'Oriuntur autem variis temporibus ac diebus et secundum climata;', '', 1716, 'But they rise at different times and days also according to the climes', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.11.2', 2019, '1.54', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1150, 'GE6 9 USAN2 lu2.TUR GUD(?) x x', '', 271, 'Night of the 9th, evening watch, the child ... .', 'BM 36796 (BH 15)', 'horoscope', 'Babylon', '2nd century BCE (Date of birth in horoscope: S.E. 109 XI.9 = -201 Feb.4)', 'Rochberg, F. 1998. Babylonian Horoscopes. Transactions of the American Philosophical Society, 88, 1–164.', '', '4', 369, '97', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (439, 'DIŠ ⌈MUL ša2⌉ ina ⌈SAG⌉.KI mul.MAR.GID2.DA GUB-zu mul.U8 d.A-a', '', 406, '¶ The star which stands in the front part of the Wagon: the Ewe, Aja.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 18', 548, '33', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (175, 'ὁμορόησις δέ ἐστιν, ὅταν ἐν τοῖς αὐτοῖς ὁρίοις ἀστέρες ὦσιν ἤτοι κατὰ σῶμα ἢ σχῆμα ἢ ἀλλήλους ἐφορῶσιν ὁρίοις ἀστέρος τοῦ αὐτοῦ.', '', 181, '“Neighboring” is whenever planets are in the same terms, that is, either bodily or in configuration, or are in aspect with each other in the terms of the same planet', 'Antiochus, Fragments', 'astrological treatise', 'Athens', '1st cent. BCE/1st cent. CE', 'CCAG I', '', '40', 86, '159 (cf. VIII.3, 107)', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (173, 'ὁμοροοῦν λέγεται ζῴδιον τῇ Σελήνῃ τὸ ἐπαναφερόμενον ἐφ’ ὃ φέρεται· τὸ γὰρ αὐτὸ καὶ παράκολλον καλεῖται· ἀποσαλεῦον δὲ τὸ μηδὲ ὁροούμενον ὑπὸ τῆς Σελήνης ζῴδιον', '', 179, 'A zodiac sign is said to “be a neighbor” to the Moon that is in a following position (epanapheromai) to the (sign) in which (the Moon) is: the same (sign) is called “attached”; the zodiac sign that has no contiguity(?) with the Moon is “anchored offshore”', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 257, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (20, '', 'ꜣbd-2 šmw pꜣ mꜣe', 64, 'Payni: Leo', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521.9', 'astronomical list', '', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '', 63, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (440, 'DIŠ mul.MU.BU.KEŠ2.DA d.A-num GAL-u2 ša2 AN-e', '', 407, '¶ The Hitched Yoke, great Anu of heaven.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 19', 549, '33', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (510, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 EGIR-šu2 GUB-zu mul.lu-lim SUKAL MUL.MUL', '', 469, '¶ The star which stands behind it: the Stag, the minister of the Stars.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 31', 628, '36', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (551, '[DIŠ MUL.MEŠ um-mu-l]u-tu4 ša2 ina KUN mul.UR.GU.LA [GUB-zu sis]-sin-nu d.E4-ru6 d.Zar-pa-ni-tu4', '', 496, '¶ The scintillating stars which stand in the tail of the Lion: The Frond (of the date palm) of Eru, Zarpanitu.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 10-11', 666, '31-32', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (148, 'βοηθοὶ δὲ λέγονται ἀστέρες οἱ συλλαμβανόμενοι ἢ ἐπιμαρτυροῦντες ἢ μεσεμβολοῦντες', '', 158, 'Collaborators are the (stars) that travel together (are in conjunction?), and assistants are those that meet each other (in adjacent signs?)', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 220, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (689, '(15) kun-nu u [nu]-bal-kut ME ana ME kun-nu
(16)  la nu-bal-kut 1-en ME LA₂ tur-ru la nu-bal-kut ME ana ME tur-ru u nu-bal-kut 1-en ME TAB', '', 616, '(15) (The month) is full and (the day) is transgressed: the day (corresponds) to the (same) day. (The month) is full (16) (and the day) is not transgressed: you subtract 1 day. (The month) is hollow and (the day) is not transgressed: the day (corresponds) to the (same) day. (The month) is hollow and (the day) is transgressed: you add 1 day.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. ii 15-16', 810, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (863, '...] ζ μθ λ .η λδ Παχω [...', '', 762, '...] 7 49 30 x8 34 Pacho(n) [...', 'P. Oxy. LXI 4212', 'mathematical astronomy: five-day almanac', 'Oxyrhynchus', 'after 218 CE', 'Jones, A. (ed.), 1999. Astronomical papyri from Oxyrhynchus (P. Oxy. 4133-4300a), Volumes I and II. Philadelphia: American Philosophical Society.', 'https://archive.org/details/astronomicalpapy0001jone', '9', 956, 'I: 226 + II: 314-315', 'A horizontal bar is written above and to the right of the ω to indicate that it is an abbreviation.');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (698, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 ina A2-šu2 GUB-zu mul.giš.GAN2.UR3 giš.TUKUL ša2 d.A-E2 ša2 ina lib3-bi-šu2 ZU.AB i-bar-ru-u2', '', 625, '¶ The star which stands at its side: the Harrow, the weapon of Mār-bīti, by means of which he sees the subterranean waters.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 23-24', 820, '43-44', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (722, 'τὸ δὲ τὴν Σελήνην ἀπερρευκέναι τῆς Ἀφροδίτης καὶ τῷ Διὶ συνάπτειν τὰς τύχας συνῆπτε τοῦ τε ἀποστείλαντος καὶ τοῦ ὑποδεξαμένου', '', 647, 'The fact that the Moon had left contact with Venus and was making contact with Jupiter placed the fortunes of the person who sent and the person who received (a gift, the occasion of this catarchic horoscope)', 'CCAG VI', 'horoscope', '', '', '(GH L 483)', '', 'p. 66', 840, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (677, '(11'') 30.45 U₄.⸢MEŠ⸣ [u 11.3.20]
(12'')  U₄.MEŠ ana UGU a-ḫa-miš₂ GAR.GAR-ma 41.48.20 U₄.MEŠ GABA.RI MU.AN.NA GAR-[an]', '', 607, '(11'') You accumulate 30;45 (error for 30;55) ‘days’ and [11;3,20] together, 41;48,20 (error for 41;58,20) ‘days’ you put down as the value of the ‘year’.', 'BM 34081+ (BMAPT No. 18)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 250-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. i 11''-12''', 800, '252-253', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2223, 'IZI GE₆ 22 EN e SA₄ ša₂ ABSIN 1 KUŠ₃ 8 SI', '', 1764, 'Month V, night of the 22nd, first part of the night, it was 1 cubit 8 fingers above the bright star of the furrow', 'IM 44152', 'astronomical diaries and related texts: planetary excerpt', 'Uruk', '160-172 SE', 'Hunger, H. 2001. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. V. Lunar and Planetary Texts. Vienna, Austria: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wis­senschaften.', '', 'III 2''-3''', 2067, '352-353', 'EN occurs in two texts from Uruk, A 3456 and IM 44152; there I assumed an abbreviation or variant for USAN "first part of the night." (Hunger ADRT 5, 352; ADRT 6, XI).');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (142, 'χρηματιστικὰ ζῴδια λέγεται τὰ δʹ κέντρα καὶ αἱ τούτων ἐπαναφοραί', '', 147, 'Active zodiac signs are called the 4 cardinal points (kentra) and their following places (epanaphorai)', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 210, '225', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2380, 'quin etiam Arcitenens, qui te, Capricorne, sub ipso
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1149, 'διὸ οἰκοδεσποτήσει τὸ διάθε̣μα', '', 1036, 'Therefore it (Mercury) will be the house-master of the (natal) chart.', 'P.Lond. I 130', 'horoscope', '', '81 CE', '(GH 81)', '', '162–164', 1244, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (745, 'ἔσχον ἀρχὴν μὲν τοῦ θʹ τόπου· τουτέστι τοῦ καλουμένου θεοῦ· τέλος δὲ τοῦ ηʹ ὃν καὶ τόπον ἀργὸν καλοῦσι', '', 666, '(By these calculations) I obtained the beginning of the 9th place—that is, the one called God—and the end of the 8th, which they also call the Idle place', 'CCAG VIII.2', 'horoscope', '', '', '', '', 'p. 68', 860, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (723, 'τὸ δὲ τὴν Σελήνην ἀπερρευκέναι τῆς Ἀφροδίτης καὶ τῷ Διὶ συνάπτειν τὰς τύχας συνῆπτε τοῦ τε ἀποστείλαντος καὶ τοῦ ὑποδεξαμένου', '', 648, 'The fact that the Moon had left contact with Venus and was making contact with Jupiter placed the fortunes of the person who sent and the person who received (a gift, the occasion of this catarchic horoscope)', 'CCAG VI', 'horoscope', '', '', '(GH L 486)', '', 'p. 66', 841, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (149, 'NIM u₃ BUR₃ ša₂ sin ana DU₃-ka', '', 123, 'In order for you to compute the "height" and "depth" of Sin', 'BM 41004', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', '', 'Brack-Bernsen & Hunger 2005/6, AfO 51, 96-107', '', '', 168, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (763, '(13'') BE-ma UD.DA.ZAL-e u₄-mi ⌈ITI⌉ u MU.AN.NA ana IGI-[ka]
(14'') 1.40 UD.DA.ZAL.LA₂-e u₄-me ana ITI IL₂-ma
(15'') 50 UD.DA.ZAL.LA₂-e ITI IGI', '', 680, '(13'') In order for you to see the udazallu-coefficient for day, [month], and year:
(14'') you multiply 1.40, the udazallu-coefficient for a day, by a month, and
(15'') you find 50, the udazallu-coefficient for a month.', 'VAT 9412+11279 (Mul.Apin HH)', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', 'Assur', '687 BC', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 13''-15'' (Mul.Apin Tablet II ii 13-15)', 872, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (150, 'ina 9 MU.MEŠ 6 KUŠ₃ DAGAL ma-la-ka ul-tu NIM ana BUR₃ BUR₃-ma', '', 159, 'In 9 years it goes down 6 cubits, the width of the path from "height" to "depth", and (...)', 'BM 41004', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', '', 'Brack-Bernsen & Hunger 2005/6, AfO 51, 96-107', '', 'obv. 15', 221, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1931, 'Sane extra ceteros climacteras etiam septimi anni et noni per omne vitae tempus multiplicata ratione currentes naturali quadam et latenti ratione variis hominem periculorum discriminibus semper afficiunt,', '', 1717, 'Aside from other climacteric periods, also every seventh and ninth year and their multiples through all life in some natural and hidden ways affect men with various dangerous crises.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '4.20.3', 2020, '1.258', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (825, '(15'') ki-i DIŠ.U₄ ša₂ SIG al-⸢la BE⸣ BAR.NUN u 2 ḪAB-rat DIRI-at BE BAR.NUN u 2 ḪAB-rat
(16'') TA lib₃-bi-šu₂ LA₂ ana ⸢GI₆ E-bi⸣', '', 743, '(15'') If the DIŠ.U₄ of depth exceeds the elongation and the ṣiliptu-coefficient and the 2 for the disk you subtract the elongation and the ṣiliptu-coefficient and the 2 for the disk (16'') from it. You call it GI₆.', 'MMA 86.11.363 (BMAPT No. 61G)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-100 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. 15''-16''', 933, '406-407', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (102, 'ina 9 MU.MEŠ NIM ina 9 MU.MEŠ i-šap-pil', '', 124, 'In 9 years it goes up, in 9 years it goes down.', 'BM 41004', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', '', 'Brack-Bernsen & Hunger 2005/6, AfO 51, 96-107', '', 'obv. 10', 169, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (108, 'νειόθι δὲ σπείρης μεγάλας ἐπιμαίεο Χηλάς· ἀλλ’ αἱ μὲν φαέων ἐπιδευέες, οὐδὲν ἀγαυαί', '', 135, 'At the bottom of the coil (sc. of the Crown), search for the great Claws, but they are poor in illumination, without any brilliance', 'Aratus, Phainomena', 'astronomy', '', 'mid 3rd cent. BCE', '', '', '89–90', 183, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (164, '', 'nth rḫ n šꜥ.w n pꜣ 5 sw ꜥnḫ.w ḥnꜥ gm pꜣ wš n ỉr ꜥb.t n p(ꜣ) rꜥ ỉꜥḥ', 170, '... who knows the appearance of the 5 living stars and find the time of obscuration of the sun and the moon', 'Graf.Phil. 410', 'inscription', 'Philae', '3rd cent. CE', 'Griffith, F.Ll.,   Catalogue of the Demotic Graffiti of the Dodecaschoenus (Oxford, 1935 - 1937)', '', '7-8', 247, '26-31', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (699, 'DIŠ 2 MUL.MEŠ ša2 EGIR-šu2 GUB.MEŠ2-zu d.Šullat2 u d.Ḫaniš2 d.UTU u d.IŠKUR', '', 626, '¶ The two stars which stand behind it: Šullat and Ḫaniš, Šamaš and Adad.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 25', 821, '44', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (577, '', 'ḥsb.t 24(.t) ỉbd-4 šmw sw 21 (wnw.t) 8.t n hrw | pꜣ rꜥ mꜣy 21 sbkꜣ | ỉꜥḥ gnḥḏ 6 (ḥr)-tšy kꜣ 12 sbkꜣ | ḥsb.t 1 mḥ-2.t wꜣḥ', 522, 'Regnal year 24, Mesore 21, 8th (hour) of the day | the Sun in Leo 21°: (terms of) Mercury| the Moon in Cancer 6°: (terms of) Mars; Taurus 12°: (terms of) Mercury; Numbering year 1, waning: (it) adds.', 'O. Athribis 17-36-5/1741', 'horoscope', 'Athribis', '6 BCE', 'Escolano-Poveda, 2022, Astrologica Athribitana: Four Demotic-Hieratic Horoscopes from Athribis (O. Athribis 17-36-5/1741 and ANAsh. Mus.D.O.633 Reedited), Journal for the History of Astronomy, 53.1, 49-82.', '', '1-4', 691, '57', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (678, 'GABA.RI U₄.NA₂.A ana DU₃-ka', '', 607, 'In order for you to compute the counterpart of the day of disappearance (of SIn).', 'AO 6455 (TCL VI 11 = TU 11)', 'collection of astrological and astronomical rules', 'Uruk', 'ca. 200 BCE', 'Brack-Bernsen, Lis, and Hunger, Hermann. 2002. TU 11. A Collection of Rules for the Prediction of Lunar Phases and of Month Lengths. SCIAMVS 3: 3–90.', '', 'rev. 8', 801, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (293, '', 'pꜣ wn pꜣ 5 syw ꜥnḫ', 103, 'The list of the five living stars', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521', 'astronomical list', 'Thebes (?)', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '1', 144, '121', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1049, 'non ideo in diurnis genituris in oportunis locis positi [...]', '', 939, 'if placed in a diurnal nativity in no good places [...]', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.7.2', 1143, '1.49', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2381, 'quosque Aries prae se mittit, duo tempora Pisces
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (441, 'DIŠ mul.MAR.GID2.DA.AN.NA d.Dam-ki-an-na', '', 408, '¶ The Wagon of Heaven, Damkianna.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 20', 550, '34', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (161, '(6) KI BAR.NUN ša₂ l[u-maš] (7) ša₂-šu₂ ki TAB TAB ki LA₂ LA₂ ana muḫ-ḫi a-ḫa-miš₂ GAR.GAR-ma ½-šu₂-nu GIŠ-ma ana BAR.NUN ⸢GAR⸣-[an]', '', 167, '(6) You add it with the corresponding ṣiliptu-coefficient for the zod[iac] if it is increasing, subtract if it is decreasing. You accumulate (them) together, compute half of it and put it down as the ṣiliptu-coefficient.', 'BM 35399 (BMAPT No. 61A)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'Obv. 6-7', 237, '396', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (46, 'Δίδυμοί εἰσιν ἀρσενικοί, δίσωμοι, εὔφωνοι, οἶκος Ἑρμοῦ, ἀνωφερεῖς, ἀερώδεις, θηλυνόμενοι, δουλελεύθεροι, στειρώδεις, δημόσιοι.', '', 92, 'Gemini is masculine, two-bodied, good-voiced, a house of Mercury, ascending, of air, effeminate, of freedmen, barren, of the (common) people', 'Vettius Valens', 'astrology', '', '2nd century CE', '', '', '1.2.18', 115, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (30, '⸢2.34⸣ GU4 15 22.35.37.30 MAŠ  ŠU2', '', 73, '(Year) 2,34, month II, (day) 15, (in) 22;35,37,30 Gemini it (Jupiter) sets.', 'BM 43023+ (Steele 2010 Text L)', 'mathematical astronomy: synodic table', 'Babylon', 'ca. 200-170 BCE', 'Steele, J. 2010, Newly Identified Lunar and Planetary Tables from Babylon in the British Museum, SCIAMVS  11,  211-239.', '', 'obv. 10''', 83, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1290, '[...] quando et ad quas stellas plena feratur <vel> minuta luminibus, qualiter conditionis suae stellis iungatur, quando in eadem parte posita synodica se copulatione coniungat [...]', '', 1147, 'when and towards which planets it moves when waning, under which conditions it aspects the planets, when it comes into synodic aspect [= conjunction] in the same degree [...]', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '4.1.10', 1383, '1.199-200', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (558, 'DIŠ MUL.MEŠ um-mu-lu-tu4 ša2 ina GABA mul.lu-lim GUB.MEŠ-zu d.Ḫar-ri-ru d.TIR.AN.NA', '', 501, '¶ The scintillating stars which stand in the chest of the Stag: The Vole, the Rainbow god.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 32-33', 672, '36', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (158, '30 ME ina IGI-at ŠU₂-šu₂ ša₂ ME 6 ZI-ma ŠU₂', '', 164, '30 days before its setting it (Saturn) moves (0);6 per day, then it sets.', 'AO 6477 (BMAPT No. 42)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 200 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 12', 232, '312-315', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (622, 'Ἥλιος, Ἑρμῆς Ταύρῳ, Σελήνη Ὑδροχόῳ, Κρόνος, Ἀφροδίτη Κριῷ, Ζεὺς Παρθένῳ, Ἄρης Ἰχθύσιν, ὡροσκόπος Λέοντι. τὸν μὲν οὖν Ἥλιον εὕρομεν τριγώνῳ Ἀφροδίτης καὶ Σελήνης, τὴν δὲ Ἀφροδίτην ἐν ἀποκλίματι', '', 558, 'Sun, Mercury in Taurus, Moon in Aquarius, Saturn, Venus in Aries, Jupiter in Virgo, Mars in Pisces, Ascendant in Leo. We found the Sun in the triangle of Venus and the Moon, and Venus in a falling place', 'Vettius Valens', 'horoscope', '', '(GH L 83)', '', '', '2.22.17–18', 737, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (34, '[... ki?] ⸢iz⸣-ku-u₂ MUL₂.BABBAR E-a ina 10 UŠ ME ana ŠU₂ šamaš₂', 'kizkū MUL₂.BABBAR E-a ina 10 UŠ ME ana ŠU₂ šamaš₂', 80, '[... when?] it had cleared, Jupiter came out; (the eclipse began) at 10° before sunset', 'BM 40122 (LBAT 0218)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '367 BCE', 'Sachs, Abraham, Strassmaier, Johann N.,  Pinches, Theophilus. G. (1955). Late Babylonian astronomical and related texts. Brown University studies. J. Koch, AfO 38/39 103-107; Sachs, Abraham J., Hunger, Hermann. Astronomical Diaries 1, no. -304; Reiner, Fs Borger (CM 10) p 298.', 'http://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/adsd/corpus#X103670.4', 'o.8''.', 90, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (12, 'Ἑρμῆς Δία τριγωνίζων μεγάλων πράξεων δηλωτικός', '', 58, 'Mercury being in triangular (trine) aspect with Jupiter is indicative of great business affairs', 'Vettius Valens', 'astrological treatise', '', '2nd cent. CE', '', '', '2.17.50', 50, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (68, '(2) TA 1 A EN 16 MAŠ₂ 1.46 TAB (3) 16 MAŠ₂ DIB-iq GAM 20 DU-ma TAB', '', 101, 'From 1 Leo until 16 Capricorn you add 1,46. (If) it passes 16 Capricorn you multiply by 0;20 and add.', 'AO 6477 (BMAPT No. 42)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', '', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'obv. 1-2', 140, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (33, 'DIŠ mul2.GIR2.TAB Dil-mun u Bar-⸢sipa.ki⸣', '', 77, '¶ The Scorpion: Dilmun and Borsippa.', 'BM 47494', 'astrological compendium', 'Babylon?', '464-337 BCE', 'Hunger, H. 2004. Stars, Cities, and Predictions. Pp. 16–32 in Studies in the History of the Exact Sciences in Honour of David Pingree, eds. Charles Burnett, Jan Hogendijk, Kim Plofker and Michio Yano. Leiden: Brill.', '', 'obv. 10', 88, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (552, 'DIŠ mul.DINGIR.GUB.BA.MEŠ šu-ut E2-kur', '', 497, '¶ The Standing Gods of Ekur.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 23', 667, '34', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (64, '(14'') SAG.UŠ in AB.⸢SIN₂⸣ dil-bat ina KUN.ME ⸢GUB.ME-ma⸣ (15'') A.AN u A.KAL ⸢MAḪ⸣', '', 99, 'Saturn stands in the Furrow (Virgo?), Venus in the Tails (Pisces?), then strong rain and flood.', 'BM 36353+36647', 'astrology', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', '', '', 'obv. ii'' 14''-15''', 135, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (37, 'BE-ma d.Ṣal ina UR.A lu ina GIR2.TAB lu ina MAŠ.TAB.GAL.GAL lu ina ALLA UŠ-ma GUR4', '', 81, 'If Mars is stationary in Leo or in Scorpio or in Gemini or in Cancer and is bright (...)', 'O 176 (TCL VI 13 = TU 13)', 'late astrology', 'Uruk', '250-150 BCE', 'Rochberg, F., 1987. TCL 6 13: Mixed Traditions in Late Babylonian Astrology, Zeitschrift für Assyriologie 77: 207-228.', '', 'obv. ii 19', 93, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (65, '3.8 ZIZ₂ 12 9.40 zib.ME UŠ', '', 99, '(Year) 3,8, (month) XI, (day) 12, 9;40 Pisces, it (Venus) is stationary.', 'BM 42799+45777', 'mathematical astronomy: synodic table', 'Babylon', 'ca. 140-120 BCE', 'Neugebauer ACT No. 421a', '', 'obv. ii(ES) 4''', 134, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (26, '', 'ꜣbd-1 pr.t nꜣ tb[[ṱ]].w', 70, 'Tybi: Pisces', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521', 'astronomical list', 'Thebes', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '131', 76, '121', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (245, 'ki NIM ana BE LA₂', '', 254, 'If it (the Moon) is high you diminish the elongation by it (the "DIŠ.UD of height").', 'BM 35399 (BMAPT No. 61A)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 11', 343, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (865, '...Π]αχ [...] ε .θ νδ [...', '', 762, '...P]ach(on) [...] 5 x9 54 [...', 'P. Oxy. LXI 4212', 'mathematical astronomy: five-day almanac', 'Oxyrhynchus', 'after 218 CE', 'Jones, A. (ed.), 1999. Astronomical papyri from Oxyrhynchus (P. Oxy. 4133-4300a), Volumes I and II. Philadelphia: American Philosophical Society.', 'https://archive.org/details/astronomicalpapy0001jone', '10', 956, 'I: 226 + II: 314-315', 'The χ is written in superscript.');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (53, 'ζωϊδίων δέ ἑ κύκλον ἐπίκλησιν καλέουσιν·
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (553, 'mul.DINGIR.TUŠ.A.MEŠ šu-ut E2-kur', '', 498, '¶ The Sitting Gods of Ekur.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 23', 668, '32', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (45, 'ζωϊδίων δέ ἑ κύκλον ἐπίκλησιν καλέουσιν·
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1933, 'Crios autem ideo a Graecis dictum est hoc signum, quod, cum <in> eo Sol fuerit, inter diem et noctem quodammodo iudicat, quod crinein dicitur, et quod in eo signo inter hiemem positus et aestatem ipse rursus iudicetur.', '', 1719, 'This sign is called κριός by the Greeks because when the Sun is in it, it judges between day and night, as it were, which is called κρίνειν, and because located in that sign between winter and summer it is judged likewise.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.10.3', 2022, '1.53', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (18, '', 'ꜣbd-4 pr.t nꜣ ḥtr.w', 61, 'Pharmouthi: Gemini', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521.8', 'astronomical list', '', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '', 59, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (47, 'ἔστι δὲ ἐν τούτῳ τὰ μέσα τοῦ Καρκίνου καὶ τὰ διὰ τοῦ σώματος κατὰ μῆκος τοῦ Λέοντος', '', 93, 'In it (sc. the Tropic of Cancer) are the middle of Cancer and the width-wise cross-section of the body of Leo', 'Eudoxus apud Hipparchus', 'astronomy', '', '4th cent. BCE', '', '', '1.2.18', 117, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (50, 'ἔστι δὲ ἐν τούτῳ τὰ μέσα τοῦ Καρκίνου καὶ τὰ διὰ τοῦ σώματος κατὰ μῆκος τοῦ Λέοντος', '', 94, 'In it (sc. the Tropic of Cancer) are the middle of Cancer and the width-wise cross-section of the body of Leo', 'Eudoxus apud Hipparchus', 'astronomy', '', '4th cent. BCE', '', '', '1.2.18', 120, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (276, 'iti.GAN he₂-gal₂-lu u nu-uḫ-šu', '', 270, 'Kislīmu, abundance and happiness', 'KAV 218', 'astrolabe', 'Nineveh', '', 'Casaburi, M. C. 2003. Tre-stelle-per-ciascun (-mese): l''Astrolabio B: edizione filologica. Annali/Supplemento', '', 'a iii 6', 368, '41', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (737, '', 'ḥn=f n=w ḏd gšp r tꜣ p.t ỉ.nw r pꜣ ỉtm m-ỉr dỉ.t ḥp md.t ỉw=s ḫpr [... | ...] nꜣ rmṯ.w ꜥš=w nꜣy=w sẖꜣ.w gšp=w r tꜣ p.t nw=w r pꜣ ỉtm ỉ.ỉr=w gm pꜣ syw n wsỉr r ḫꜣꜥ=f tꜣy=f mỉ.t ...', 83, 'He ordered them: "Observe the sky and look at the disc. Do not allow that matters are hidden ... [... | ...] the people. They read their scriptures, they observed the sky, and they looked at the disc. They found that the Star of Osiris, in that it had left its path ..."', 'P.Carlsberg XI 5', 'literary text', 'Tebtunis', '1st - 2nd cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F., 2019, Isis, Thot und Arian und der Suche nach Osiris, in J. F. Quack and K. Ryholt, eds.,  Demotic Literary Texts from Tebtunis and Beyond, Copenhagen 2019, 77-138.', '', 'x+22-x+23', 95, '80-81', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (442, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 ina ṭur-ri-šu2 GUB-zu mul.IBILA.E2.MAḪ DUMU res-tu-u2 ša2 d.A-nu-um', '', 409, '¶ The star which stands in its knot: the Heir of the Sublime Temple, the first-ranking son of Anu.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 21-22', 551, '34', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (52, 'Λέων ἐστὶν ἀρρενικόν, οἶκος Ἡλίου, ἐλεύθερον, πυρῶδες, εὔκρατον, νοερόν, βασιλικόν, ἑδραῖον, ἀγαθόν, ἀνωφερές, εὐμετάβολον, στερεόν, ἡγεμονικόν, πολιτικόν, ἀρκτικόν, ὀργίλον', '', 94, 'Leo is a masculine (sign), a house of the Sun, of free men, of fire, temperate, intellectual, royal, firm-seated, good, ascending, variable, firm, hegemonic, political, imperious, irascible', 'Vettius Valens', 'astrology', '', '2nd century CE', '', '', '1.2.40', 121, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1481, '(16'') 1.59.9.15.33.20 LA₂ 12.⸢4⸣8.53.20 LA₂ A.RA₂ 11', '', 1308, '(16'') 1,59;9,15,33,20, decreasing, 12;48,53,20, subtractive, times 11.', 'BM 35564+ (BMAPT No. 79)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'obv. ii'' 16''', 1571, '458', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1934, 'Quanta autem sit temporum distributio, breviter ostendemus: Sol accipit menses XIX, Luna menses XXV, Saturnus menses XXX, Iuppiter menses XII, Mars menses XV, Venus menses VIII, Mercurius menses XX.', '', 1720, 'We will show briefly how the distribution of times works: The Sun takes 19 months, the Moon 25 months, Saturn 30 months, Jupiter 12 months, Mars 15 months, Venus 8 months, Mercury 20 months.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.27.1', 2023, '1.76', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (785, '(8) 5 TAB ša₂ zib
(9) 5 TAB ša₂ ḪUN bi-rit TAB ana TAB ia-a-nu', '', 702, '(8) The addition for Pisces is 5, (9) the addition for Aries is 5, the difference from addition to addition is nothing.', 'BM 36722 (BMAPT No. 52)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'Seleucid', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. ii 8-9', 894, '348-349', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (746, 'ἔσχον ἀρχὴν μὲν τοῦ θʹ τόπου· τουτέστι τοῦ καλουμένου θεοῦ· τέλος δὲ τοῦ ηʹ ὃν καὶ τόπον ἀργὸν καλοῦσι', '', 667, '(By these calculations) I obtained the beginning of the 9th place—that is, the one called God—and the end of the 8th, which they also call the Idle place', 'CCAG VIII.2', 'horoscope', '', '', '', '', 'p. 68', 861, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (38, '', 'ỉw=f ḫpr r wn sw nfr nw r-r=f', 83, 'If a beneficent star looks at it', 'P.Carlsberg 81', 'astrological treatise', 'Tebtunis', '2nd cent. CE', 'Winkler, A. 2016. Some Astrologers and their Handbooks in Demotic Egyptian. In The Circulation of Astronomical Knowledge in the Ancient World, ed. J. M. Steele. Leiden: Brill: ###', '', '', 95, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (89, '10 GIR₂.TAB 2.40 ša₂ al 10 GIR₂.TAB DIRI A.RA₂ 24 ⸢DU⸣ TA 2.40 LA₂', '', 77, '10 Scorpio: 2,40, (the amount) by which it exceeds 10 Scorpio you multiply by 0;24, subtract from 2,40.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'Obv. i 9''', 88, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (29, '(obv. 43) TA mul2.SUḪUR.MAŠ2 EN mul2.ḪUN.GA2 (obv. 44) 2 ŠU.2.MEŠ LA2-ṭi', '', 72, 'From the Goat-Fish until the Hired Worker it (the market rate) will decrease by two thirds.', 'W 22246a (SpTU I 94)', 'astrological compendium', 'Uruk', 'ca. 320 BCE', 'Hunger, H. 1976. Spätbabylonische Texte aus Uruk I. Ausgrabungen der Deutschen Forschungsgemeinschaft in Uruk-Warka 9. Berlin: Gebr. Mann Verlag.', '', 'obv. 43-44', 81, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1025, 'in quibus singuli imperium habent ac domicilium constitutum.', '', 918, 'in these [signs] they have rulership and their house.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.2.1', 1123, '1.42', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (57, '⸢1-me.2⸣1 ⸢A⸣  BAR 1⸢6.30⸣ dil-bat ŠU2 ⸢6 MUL2 IGI⸣', '', 71, '(Year) 1 hundred 21, (which has a month) XII2, (month) I, (day) 16;30, Dilbat (Venus), west, 6 Taurus, appearance (Evening First).', 'A 3415 (ACT No. 400)', 'mathematical astronomy: synodic table', 'Uruk', 'ca. 201 BCE', 'Neugebauer ACT', '', 'obv. 7', 79, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (92, '30 šu-uš-ša2-an be2-e-ri', '', 80, '30 šuššān is a bēru.', 'W 23281', 'mathematical compendium', 'Uruk', 'ca. 445-385 BCE', 'Ossendrijver 2022, On the unit UŠ = šuššān, NABU 2022/2, No. 68, 156–157', '', 'obv. i 27', 160, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1406, 'Sed cum Saturnus ad hoc idem signum id est ad Scorpionem reversus fuerit, erunt fortiores', '', 1254, 'But when Saturn returns to that same sign—i. e. to Scorpio—they will be stronger', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '5.3.39', 1498, '2.42', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (91, '(9'') ina GIR₂ u PA 1 ⸢TAB⸣ (10'') ša₂ al 30 PA DIRI (11'') A.RA₂ 1.30 D[U]', '', 119, 'In Scorpio and Sagittarius you add 1,(0), (the amount) by which it exceeds 30 Sagittarius you multiply by 1;30.', 'BM 33048 (BMAPT No. 43)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'Rev.(?) i'' 9''-11''', 157, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (700, 'DIŠ MUL ša2 EGIR-šu2-nu GUB-zu GIM d.E2-a KUR-ḫa GIM d.E2-a ŠU2.MEŠ mul.Nu-muš-da d.IŠKUR', '', 627, '¶ The star which stands behind them rises like Ea and sets like Ea: Numušda, Adad.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 26-27', 83, '44-45', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (66, '(12) TA 26 RIN2 EN 10 zib 1.46.40 TAB 10 (13) zib DIB-iq GAM 6 DU LA2', '', 99, 'From 26 Libra until 10 Pisces you add 1;46,40, (if) it passes 10 Pisces you multiply by 0;6, subtract.', 'AO 6477', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Uruk', 'ca. 250-150 BCE', 'Ossendrijver 2012 No. 42', '', 'obv. 12-13', 134, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2, 'TA 13 ABSIN0 EN 27 zib ITI ana ITI 2.⸢6⸣.15.42 TAB u LA2', '', 4, 'From 13 Virgo until 27 Pisces month by month 2,6;15,42 add and subtract.', 'BM 55530 (Ossendrijver 2012 No. 60) obv. 8''', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', '', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', '', 9, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (572, '⸢ITU BI U₄⸣ 13 IZI.ŠUB ina KI-ti₃ TIN.TIR.⸢KI⸣', '', 515, 'That month, (on day) 13, a fall of fire in the district of Tintir.', 'BM 34938+ (ADRT II No. -197C)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '198 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 5', 684, '248-249', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (56, 'SAG GI6 sin ina IGI is le10 4 SI LA2 USAN is le10 ana ŠA3 sin KU4', '', 71, 'Beginning of the night, Sin was balanced 4 fingers in front of the jaw of the bull; first part of the night, the jaw of the bull entered Sin.', 'BM 34105+ (ADRT 2 No. -253B1)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', 'Seleucid Era 58 month VIII (254 BCE)', 'Hunger & Sachs ADRT 1', '', 'obv. 9''', 130, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (277, '¶ iti.AB EZE[N  A]N.N[A ]', '', 277, 'Ṭebētu, the festival of Anu', 'KAV 218', 'astrolabe', 'Nineveh', '', 'Casaburi, M. C. 2003. Tre-stelle-per-ciascun (-mese): l''Astrolabio B: edizione filologica. Annali/Supplemento', '', 'a iii 11', 379, '41', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (511, 'DIŠ MUL SA5 ne2-bu-u2 ša2 ina BIR mul.LU.LIM GUB-zu mul.ZU2.MUŠ.I3.KU2.E', '', 470, '¶ The bright red star which stands in the kidney of the Stag: The Deleter.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'i 34-35', 629, '36-37', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (304, 'ina 18 ME TA MAR ana KUR ZALAG₂', '', 258, 'In 18 (UŠ) of daytime it (solar eclipse) cleared from west to east.', 'Rm 712 (ADRT II No. -241)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '242 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'obv.? 6''', 472, '76-77', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (90, '(9'') ina GIR₂ u PA 1 ⸢TAB⸣ (10'') ša₂ al 30 PA DIRI (11'') A.RA₂ 1.30 D[U]', '', 77, 'In Scorpio and Sagittarius you add 1,(0), (the amount) by which it exceeds 30 Sagittarius you multiply by 1;30.', 'BM 33048 (BMAPT No. 43)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'Rev.(?) i'' 9''-11''', 88, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (93, 'DU₃-šu₂ ša₂ NIM u SIG ša₂ sin AB₂ ana AB₂ 12 DAGAL ma-lak ᵈsin 2.24 MURUB₄-ti qaq-qar ki-ṣa-ri', '', 120, '’
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (100, 'šu-qa u šup-lu ša₂ ᵈsin KIN.KIN-ma', '', 123, 'The ''height'' and ''depth'' of Sin you investigate, and (...)', 'BM 35325 (LBAT 1600)', 'astrology', 'Babylon', 'ca. 450-50 BCE', 'Sachs, Abraham, Strassmaier, Johann N.,  Pinches, Theophilus. G. (1955). Late Babylonian astronomical and related texts.', '', 'rev. 9''', 168, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (39, '', 'ỉw=f ḫpr ỉw=f nw r ỉꜥḥ', 83, 'If it looks at the moon', 'P.Carlsberg 81', 'astrological treatise', 'Tebtunis', '2nd cent. CE', 'Winkler, A. 2016. Some Astrologers and their Handbooks in Demotic Egyptian. In The Circulation of Astronomical Knowledge in the Ancient World, ed. J. M. Steele. Leiden: Brill: ###', '', '', 95, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (255, '6 KI si-man IGI-u₂ TAB', '', 260, 'You add 6,(0) with the previous time.', 'BM 35399 (BMAPT No. 61A)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 13', 354, '398-399', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (802, '', 'tꜣy⸗s rnp.t mḥ 19 rnp.t n ꜥb tꜣy n ḥꜣ.ṱ⸗s pḥ.ṱ⸗s ỉr=s nmy ỉ.ỉr-ḥr [...', 717, 'Her 19th year: It is a year of miasma at the beginning and the end. She will be a flaming star before [...', 'P.Carlsberg XI 22', 'celestial divination', 'Tebtunis', '1st to 2nd century CE', 'Quack, J.F, 2019, Prognose über Desaster-Jahre, in K. Ryholt and J.F. Quack, eds, Demotic Literary Texts from Tebtunis and Beyond; Copenhagen, 273-281.', '', '5', 909, '279', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (248, '4 A.RA₂ 3 : 12 : 12 man-za-za ša₂ U₄ 1', '', 256, '4 times 3 (is) 12; 12 (is) the NA of day 1.', 'BM 42961+', 'commentary', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2014, Some new results on a commentary to Enūma Anu Enlil Tablet 14, NABU 2014/4, No. 101, 158–161.', '', 'obv. 10', 345, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (162, '', 'sẖ ḥm-nṯr n spd.t ỉmy-r(ꜣ) mšꜥ n ỉꜥḥ wꜥb n p(ꜣ) 5 sbꜣ ꜥnḫ.w', 168, 'Written by the prophet of Sothis, overseer of the moon''s movement, and wrist of the five living stars.', 'Graf.Phil. 421', 'inscription', 'Philae', '3rd cent. CE', 'Griffith, F.Ll.,  1935-1937,  Catalogue of the Demotic Graffiti of the Dodecaschoenus, Oxford.', '', '14', 243, '26-31', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (95, '(1) dil-b]at TA muḫ-ḫi UŠ ⸢ar₂⸣-tu₂ ina 2.⸢8⸣ [ME] (2)  2.8 ⸢KI⸣ DU', '', 120, 'Dilbat (= Venus). From the second station in 2,8 [days] the position proceeds (by) 2,8.', 'BM 33552 (BMAPT No. 9)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 400-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'obv. 1-2', 161, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1079, 'Deficit Iovis benignitas, cum infirmitate signi vel partium vel decani vel conditionis immutatione benignitas eius fuerit impedita', '', 969, 'The favorable influence of Jupiter fails when, because of the weakness of the sign, or a shift of a degree or decan or condition, his favorable influence is hindered', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.13.5', 1174, '1.56', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1935, '[...] quotienscunque Iuppiter post excessum Saturni ad oportuna geniturae venerit loca.', '', 1721, '[...] whenever Jupiter comes to the suitable places of the nativity after the departure of Saturn', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '5.4.17', 2024, '2.54-55', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (98, 'NIM u SIG ša₂ sin GAR', '', 122, 'You put down the height and depth of Sin.', 'BM 55530 (BMAPT No. 61C)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'rev. 5', 167, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (697, 'DIŠ mul.EN.TE.NA.BAR.ḪUM d.Nin-gir2-su', '', 624, '¶ The Mouse, Ningirsu.', 'BM 86378', 'schematic astronomy: mulapin', '?', 'ca. 626-539 BCE', 'Hunger, H. and Steele, J., 2019. The Babylonian Astronomical Compendium MUL.APIN. London and New York: Routledge.', '', 'ii 22', 819, '43', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (63, 'd.Be-let DINGIR.MEŠ ana d.Šul-pa-e3-a iṭ-ḫi', '', 90, 'Belet-ili came close to Jupiter', 'AO 6455 (TCL VI 11 = TU 11) 3', 'astrological compendium', 'Uruk', 'late 3rd cent BCE', 'Brack-Bernsen, Lis, and Hunger, Hermann. 2002. TU 11. A Collection of Rules for the Prediction of Lunar Phases and of Month Lengths. SCIAMVS 3: 3–90.', '', '', 108, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (110, 'ὅταν δὲ αἱ Χηλαὶ ἀνατέλλωσι, συνανατέλλει μὲν αὐταῖς ὁ ζῳδιακὸς ἀπὸ Χηλῶν μοίρας ιϛʹ ἕως Σκορπίου μοίρας ϛʹ· μεσουρανεῖ δὲ ἀπὸ Καρκίνου ιηʹ ἕως Λέοντος ιαʹ', '', 135, 'When the Claws rise, there rises with them the zodiac from 16 degrees of Libra until 6 degrees of Scorpio, and culminates (lit. is in midheaven) from 18 of Cancer until 11 of Leo', 'Hipparchus', 'astronomy', '', '2nd cent. BCE', '', '', '3.3.4', 183, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (58, '9 10.36 MAŠ.⸢MAŠ⸣', '', 73, '(Month X day) 9, 10;36 Gemini', 'U 96 (ACT No. 191)', 'mathematical astronomy: daily motion table', 'Uruk', '197 BCE (Seleucid Era year 115)', 'Neugebauer ACT No. 191', '', 'obv. col. ii'' 9', 83, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (86, '¶ iti.BAR2.ZAG.GAR mul.AŠ.IKU BAR2.AN.NA', '', 102, 'Nisannu, constellation of 1 iku(Field), the pedestal', 'K 2920+', 'astrolabe', 'Assur', '', 'Casaburi, M. C. 2003. Tre-stelle-per-ciascun (-mese): l''Astrolabio B: edizione filologica. Annali/Supplemento, p.29.', '', 'o. 17''', 143, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (312, '', 'ḥsb.t 5.t n Ꜣntwnyns | ỉbd-3 (n) šmw sw ꜥrḳy n pꜣ Wynyn pꜣ ṯꜣy-wnw.t 3.t n grḥ', 303, 'Regnal year 5 of Antoninus (Pius) | month 3 of Shemu, day 30 according to the Greeks, 3rd hour of the night', 'Griffith MSS 3.59', 'horoscope', 'Thebes (?)', '2nd cent. CE', 'A. Winkler, A Starry Summer Night in AD 142: A Theban Horoscope (Griffith MSS 3.59) in Context, in K. Donker van Heel, F.A.J. Hoogelijk, and C.J. Martin (eds), Hieratic, Demotic and Greek Studies and Text Editions: Of Making Many Books There Is No End. Festschrift for Sven P. Vleeming (Leiden:Brill), 298-308.', '', '1-2', 411, '301', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (237, '(2) [GI₆ 5 SAG GI₆ sin] (3) ina IGI MUL₂ SIG sa SAG GIR₂.TAB 2 2/3 KUŠ₃', '', 246, '(2) [Night of (day) 5, beginning of the night, Sin] (3) was 2 2/3 cubits in front of the lower star of the head of the scorpion.', 'BM 45808 (ADRT I No. -262)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '263 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'obv 3-4', 331, '366-367', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (171, 'προσνεύων λέγεται ὁ ἀκολουθῶν τῷ προερχομένῳ', '', 177, 'The (planet) following is said to be “inclining towards” the (planet) preceding it.', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '1st cent. BCE/CE?', 'CCAG VIII.4', '', '', 255, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1917, 'εἰδώλοις δ’ ἐν ὑγροῖσι Κρόνον καὶ φοίνιον Ἄρην ξυνὴν ἐξανύοντας ὁδὸν Τιτὰν ὅτε λεύσσῃ', '', 1256, 'When the Titan (the Sun) sees (is in aspect with) Saturn and bloody Mars as they complete a common path in watery zodiac signs', 'Pseudo-Manetho, Apotelesmatika', 'astrological treatise', '', '', '', '', '6.362–363', 2005, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (151, 'TA UŠ IGI 30 NINDA ZI-šu₂', '', 160, 'From the first appearance its displacement is (0;)30 nindanu.', 'BM 41043', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 300-50 BCE', 'M. Ossendrijver, 2017, New results on a Babylonian scheme for Jupiter''s motion along the zodiac, Journal of Near Eastern Studies 76, 231–247', 'https://doi.org/10.1086/693459', 'obv. 8', 224, '236', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1936, 'Hae figurae stellarum quando prosint, quando noceant, in libris posterioribus explicabimus;', '', 1722, 'We will explain in the later books when these configurations of stars are beneficial, when they are harmful', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.8.2', 2025, '1.50', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (734, '', 'ḥn=f n=w ḏd gšp r tꜣ p.t ỉ.nw r pꜣ ỉtm m-ỉr dỉ.t ḥp md.t ỉw=s ḫpr [... | ...] nꜣ rmṯ.w ꜥš=w nꜣy=w sẖꜣ.w gšp=w r tꜣ p.t nw=w r pꜣ ỉtm ỉ.ỉr=w gm pꜣ syw n wsỉr r ḫꜣꜥ=f tꜣy=f mỉ.t ...', 658, 'He ordered them: "Observe the sky and look at the disc. Do not allow that matters are hidden ... [... | ...] the people. They read their scriptures, they observed the sky, and they looked at the disc. They found that the Star of Osiris, in that it had left its path ..."', 'P.Carlsberg XI 5', 'literary text', 'Tebtunis', '1st - 2nd cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F., 2019, Isis, Thot und Arian aud der Suche nach Osiris, in J. F. Quack and K. Ryholt, eds.,  Demotic Literary Texts from Tebtunis and Beyond, Copenhagen 2019, 77-138.', '', 'Frag. 1, x+22-x+23', 852, '80-81', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (104, '', '[pꜣy-ms=w r pꜣ-nṯr]-twꜣ n ꜥ.wy (n) sḥn-ꜥnḫ pꜣy=f ꜥnḫ |', 127, '[The one who was born when Ven]us was in the House of provisions of life, his life will |', 'P.Berlin 8345', 'astrological treatise', 'Soknopaiou Nesos', '1st cent. CE to 2nd cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F., 2008, Texte aus Ägypten: Demotische, magische und divinatorische Texte. In B. Janowski and B. Wilhelm (eds), Omina, Orakel, Rituale und Beschwörungen. Texte aus der Umwelt des Alten Testaments, Neue Folge 4. Gütersloh: Gütersloher Verlagshaus.', '', 'x+1, 9', 173, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (261, '', 'pꜣy-ms=w r swgꜣ (n) ꜥ.wy (n) špšy.t ỉw=f  [r ỉr]\ nfr r šy', 265, 'The one who was born when Mercury was in the House of fortune, he will be | lucky as too fate.', 'P.Berlin 8345', 'astrological treatise', 'Soknopaiou Nesos', '1st cent. CE to 2nd cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F., 2008, Texte aus Ägypten: Demotische, magische und divinatorische Texte. In B. Janowski and B. Wilhelm (eds), Omina, Orakel, Rituale und Beschwörungen. Texte aus der Umwelt des Alten Testaments, Neue Folge 4. Gütersloh: Gütersloher Verlagshaus.', '', 'iv 10-11', 361, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (774, '', 'pꜣ gꜣy (n) šny m-sꜣ ⌈pꜣ⌉ ꜥ.wy (n) [...] ⌈nty-ỉw=w ỉr=f (n) pꜣ ⌈rmṯ⌉ mtw=w r ms.ṱ=f šꜥ-ỉr=w pꜣ šn pꜣ twtw nty-ỉw ỉꜥḥ ẖn=f', 691, 'The manner of enquiring after the house of [...] which they will make for the man who will be born. One always examines the zodiac sign in which the Moon is.', 'P.Carlsberg XI 10', 'li', 'Tebtunis', '2nd Cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F. and K. Ryholt, 2019, Petese Interpreting Astrology by Imhotep for King Nechepsos. Copenhagen, 2019, 161-183.', '', '11', 884, '165', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (709, '', 'tpy ꜣḫ.t ḏlꜣ(.t) | ỉbd-2 ꜣḫ.t pꜣ-[nty-ꜣtḥ] ỉbd-3 ꜣḫ.t pꜣ-ḥr-ꜥnḫ | ỉbd-4 ꜣḫ.t pꜣ-twtw-n-pꜣ-mw', 633, '(Month) 1 of Akhet: Scorpio; | month 2 of Akhet: ⌈Sagittarius⌉; month 3 of Akhet: Capricorn | month 4 of Akhet: Aquarius', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521', 'astronomical list', 'Thebes (?)', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '10-12', 831, '121', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (113, 'τῷ δὲ τῆς Ἀφροδίτης (...) ἐδόθη δύο ζῴδια γονιμώτατα ὄντα αἵ τε Χηλαὶ καὶ ὁ Ταῦρος', '', 135, 'To the (star) of Venus (...) have been assigned (as houses) the two zodiac-signs that are the most progenitive, the Claws and Taurus', 'Ptolemy, Tetrabiblos', 'astrology', '', '2nd cent. CE', '', '', '1.18.7', 184, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (116, 'Σκορπίος οἶκος Ἄρεως, θηλυκόν, στερεόν, ὑδατῶδες, πολύσπερμον, φθοροποιόν, κατωφερές, ἄφωνον, δουλικόν, ἀμετάβλητον, δυσωδίας αἴτιον, ὑπαρχόντων ἀφαιρετικόν, ἐκλειπτικόν, πολύχουν.', '', 137, 'Scorpio is a house of Mars, a feminine (sign), firm, of water, fertile, destructive, descending, unvoiced, of slaves, invariable, source of bad odor, remover of goods, ecliptic, manifold', 'Vettius Valens', 'astrology', '', '', '', '', '1.2.53', 187, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (106, '', 'dny.t (n) sn pꜣ-nty-ꜣtḥ', 128, 'The part of the brother: Sagittarius', 'O.Neugeb. 3', 'horoscope', 'Thebes', '1st cent. CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 116-117', '', '14', 174, '116-117', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (747, 'ζῳδίῳ Ἄ̣ρεως ὁρίοις Ἑρμ̣οῦ στοιχείῳ Διὸς ἀρρενικῷ καὶ π̣ρ̣ὸς βορρῶι ζῳδίῳ', '', 668, '(In Aries,) the zodiac sign of Mars, terms of Mercury, “element” of Jupiter, a masculine and northerly zodiac sign', 'P.Lond. I 130', 'horoscope', '', '81 CE', '(GH 81)', '', '59–63', 862, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (160, '(8) 5 TAB ša₂ zib (9) 5 TAB ša₂ ḪUN bi-rit TAB ana TAB ia-a-nu', '', 166, '(8) The addition for Pisces is 5, (9) the addition for Aries is 5, the difference from addition to addition is nothing.', 'BM 36722 (BMAPT No. 52)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. i 8-9', 236, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (152, 'TA UŠ IGI 30 NINDA ZI-šu₂', '', 161, 'From the first station its displacement is (0;)30 nindanu.', 'BM 41043', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 300-50 BCE', 'M. Ossendrijver, 2017, New results on a Babylonian scheme for Jupiter''s motion along the zodiac, Journal of Near Eastern Studies 76, 231–247', 'https://doi.org/10.1086/693459', 'obv. 4', 225, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (645, 'ϩⲛ̅ ⲥⲟⲩ ⲙⲛ̅ⲧⲁϥⲧⲉ ⲙ | ⲫⲁⲙⲉⲛⲱⲑ ⲧⲏⲥ | ⲧⲉⲧⲣⲁⲧⲏⲥ ⲓⲛⲇⲓⲕ/ | ⲁⲡⲣⲉⲣ̅ⲕⲁⲕⲉ ⲛ̅ϫ̅ⲡ | ϥⲧⲟ ⲙ̅ⲡ̅ϩⲟⲟⲩ', 'hn sou mntafte m | phamenôtʰ tês | tetratês indik/ | aperkake nčp | fto mphoou', 579, 'On the fourteenth day | of Phamenoth on the fourth (year of the) indiction, the sun was eclipsed during the | fourth hour of the day', 'O.Tur.Copt. 38', 'letter', 'Thebes', '7th cent. CE', 'J. Ray and G. Gilmore, 2006, A Fixed Point in Coptic Chronology: The Solar Eclipse of 10 March, 601, Zeitschrift für Papyrologie und Epigraphik 158, 190-192.', '', '1-5', 759, '190', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (573, 'EN.NUN ša₂ gi-ne₂-e ša₂ TA ITU.⸢NE⸣ [EN TIL] ⸢ITU⸣.APIN ša₂ MU 1 ME 43.⸢KAM₂⸣ [m.an-ti-ʾu]-uk-su LUGAL', '', 516, 'Regular watch from month V [to the end of] month VIII of year 1 hundred 43, king Antiochus.', 'BM 41581 (ADRT II No. -168A)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '169 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1989. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. II: Diaries from 261 B.C. to 165 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', '', 'rev. 22''', 685, '476-477', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (181, 'DIŠ dUTU AN.GE6 GAR ERIN2.MEŠ LUGAL UG7.MEŠ', '', 107, 'If the Sun makes an eclipse: the troops of the king will die.', 'BM 47494', 'astrological compendium', 'Babylon?', '464-337 BCE', 'Hunger, H. 2004. Stars, Cities, and Predictions. Pp. 16–32 in Studies in the History of the Exact Sciences in Honour of David Pingree, eds. Charles Burnett, Jan Hogendijk, Kim Plofker and Michio Yano. Leiden: Brill.', '', 'rev. 29', 146, '20', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (170, 'κακοῦται ἀστὴρ ὅταν μὴ εἰς ἁρμόζοντα τύχῃ παρὼν ἢ περιέχηται ὑπὸ κακοποιῶν ἢ κατ’ ἐναντίον ἢ ἐπιδέκατον· ὅτι ἀγαθοποιὰ ζῴδιά εἰσιν ὁ ὡροσκόπος, τὸ μεσουράνημα, ιαʹ, εʹ θεός, θεά· κακοποιὰ δὲ βʹ, δʹ ϛʹ, ζʹ, ⟨ηʹ⟩, ιβʹ', '', 176, 'A planet is oppressed whenever it is present in an unsuitable (place?) or is surrounded by malefics or in a relation of opposition (to them) or being “tithed” (by them): benefic zodiac signs are the Ascendant, Midheaven, the 11th (place), the 5th, God, Goddess, and malefic ones are the 2nd, 4th, 6th, 7th, <8th,> 12th (places).', 'Sarapion of Alexandria, Various Names for Configurations of the Stars', 'astrology', '', '', 'CCAG VIII.4', 'https://archive.org/details/cataloguscodipart408bruxuoft/page/226/mode/2up', '', 253, '226', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (177, 'ὡς ὁμορόησις λέγεται ὅταν ἐν τοῖς αὐτῶν ὁρίοις ἀστέρες ὦσιν ἢ κατὰ κόλλησιν ἢ κατὰ σχῆμα οἱονδήποτε ἀλλήλους ἐφορῶσιν ἐν ὁρίοις τοῦ αὐτοῦ ἀστέρος ὄντες· κενοδρομία δὲ ὅταν ἡ Σελήνη μηδενὶ συνάπτῃ μήτε ζῳδιακῶς μήτε μοιρικῶς μήτε κατὰ κόλλησιν μήτε κατὰ σχῆμα μήτε μὴν ἐντὸς λʹ μοιρῶν τῶν ἔγγιστα συναφὴν ἢ σύνοδον ποιεῖσθαι μέλλῃ· καὶ ὡς κακοῖ τὸ σχῆμα τὴν γένεσιν.', '', 182, '(Antiochus says) that it is called “neighboring” whenever planets are in their terms, or are in attachment or in aspect with each other in any configuration in the terms of the same planet. “Running empty” is whenever the Moon is not in contact with any (planet), neither with respect to zodiac signs nor with respect to degrees nor in attachment(?) nor in configuration nor even about to make a union or conjunction within the next 30 degrees, and (Antiochus says) that this configuration oppresses the nativity.', 'Antiochus, Fragments', 'astrological treatise', 'Athens', '1st cent. BCE/1st cent. CE', 'CCAG VIII.3', '', '', 260, '107', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (902, '(13'') [12.3]⸢3.5⸣1.52.47.20 MURUB₄-u₂ ša₂ TA IGI ana ⸢IGI 2⸣.44.⸢45.6⸣.46.[46.40 MURUB₄-u₂]
(14'') [ša₂ T]A ŠU₂ ana IGI 4.59.22.55.57.46.40 MURUB₄-u₂ TA ⸢IGI ana UŠ 4.49.33.50⸣
(15'') ⸢5⸣.51.6.40 MURUB₄-u₂ ša₂ TA IGI ana ŠU₂ an-na-a U₄.DA.ZAL.LA₂ ša₂ KI.MEŠ', '', 793, '(13’) [12;33],51,52,47,20, the middle one which is from appearance (FA) to appearance.
(14’) 2;44,45,6,46,[46,40, the middle one] [which is] from setting (LA) to appearance. 4;59,22,55,57,46,40 (error for 4;59,32,55,57,46,40), the middle one from appearance to [station (S1)]. 4;49,33,50, (15’)[5],51,6,40, the ‘middle one’ which is from appearance (error for station) to setting. Thus are the udazallû-coefficients for the positions.', 'BM 34676 (BMAPT No. 13)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. 13''-15''', 990, '230-231', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (346, '[iti.B]ARA2 3.20 mul2.IKU 1.30 mul2.KA5.A 45 mul2.d.AMAR.UTU', '', 326, '[Mo]nth I: 3,20 ''The Field'', 1,30 ''The Fox'', 45 Marduk.', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 1', 441, '126', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (424, 'DIŠ ina iti.APIN ina še-rim mul2.UR.IDIM 2.20 meš-ḫu im-šuḫ A.DAM ⌈BAL.MEŠ⌉-ma A.AB.BA ib-bal', '', 379, 'If in Araḫsamna during the morning-watch, ''The Mad-Dog'' - 2,20 - produced a glow; the pasture land(s) will be passed over and the sea will dry up.', 'BM 34713 (LBAT 1499)', 'schematic astronomy: ''three stars each'' + rising times', 'Babylon', '4th-2nd cent BCE', 'Horowitz, W., 2014. The Three Stars Each: The Astrolabes and Related Texts (Archiv für Orientforschung, Beiheft 33). Horn/Wien: Berger & Söhne/Institut für Orientalistik der Universität Wien.', '', 'obv. 20', 534, '127', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (868, '...]. | | χι ζ | Παῦν | [...', '', 763, '...]x | | 610 7 | Paun(i) | [...', 'P. Oxy. LXI 4157', 'mathematical astronomy: epoch table', 'Oxyrhynchus', '2nd/3rd century CE', 'Jones, A. (ed.), 1999. Astronomical papyri from Oxyrhynchus (P. Oxy. 4133-4300a), Volumes I and II. Philadelphia: American Philosophical Society.', 'https://archive.org/details/astronomicalpapy0001jone', '2', 957, 'I: 135-136 + II: 80-81', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (748, 'ἐν Ζυγῷ ζῳδίῳ ἀρ̣σενικῷ', '', 668, 'in Libra, a masculine zodiac sign', 'P.Oxy. 235', 'horoscope', '', '', '(GH 15/22)', '', '8', 862, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (36, 'MUL d.Ṣal-bat-a-nu : muš-ta-bar-ru-u2 mu-ta-nu', '', 81, 'Mars : One who makes the pestilence continue.', 'BM 42262 (5R, 46, 1)', 'star list', 'Borsippa', 'Achaemenid or Seleucid period.', 'Wee, J. Z., 2016. A Late Babylonian Astral Commentary on Marduk''s Address to the Demons, Journal of Near Eastern Studies 75.', '', '42', 93, '162', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (710, '', 'ỉbd-2 pr.t pꜣ ỉsw ỉbd-3 pr.t pꜣ kꜣ', 634, 'Month 2 of the Peret season: Aries; Month 3 of the Peret season: Taurus', 'O.Strasb.Dem. 521', 'astronomical list', 'Thebes (?)', '300 BCE - 300 CE', 'Neugebauer, O., 1943. Demotic Horoscopes, Journal of the American Oriental Society 63: 121-122', '', '7', 832, '121', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (749, 'ζῳδίῳ Ἄ̣ρεως ὁρίοις Ἑρμ̣οῦ στοιχείῳ Διὸς ἀρρενικῷ καὶ π̣ρ̣ὸς βορρῶι ζῳδίῳ', '', 669, '(In Aries,) the zodiac sign of Mars, terms of Mercury, “element” of Jupiter, a masculine and northerly zodiac sign', 'P.Lond. I 130', 'horoscope', '', '81 CE', '(GH 81)', '', '59–63', 863, '', '');
