(6)  1 U₄ 20? ZI ⸢ME NIM?⸣.A GI₆ DU TAB', '', 699, '(1) In 18 years Sin lacks(?) 2.47.23? . (2) Whatever (the amount) by which it exceeds 1,57;47,57,46,40: (3) you multiply it by (0);10,5,20 and add it with 11;36, the displacement. (4) You compute its igigubbû-coefficient, and you multiply it by 2.47.22, you multiply it by 6, and (5) you deduct it from 3.16.21, and you subtract the duration of your night, (6) 1 day of the Sun? you subtract; the time since sunrise , (the time by which) the night has progressed, you add.', 'BM 36744+ (BMAPT No. 92)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer', '', 'obv. 1-6', 891, '490', 'The meaning of igigubbû in this example is unclear.');
