(5'') ana muḫ-ḫi a-ḫa-miš₂ TAB-ma ½-šu₂ GIŠ-⸢ma⸣', '', 774, '(4'') Its procedure: the [...] width(s) of the trapezoid (5'') you add (“accumulate”) together, you compute half of it, and ...', 'BM 34757', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon?', 'ca. 350-100 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2016, Ancient Babylonian astronomers calculated Jupiters position from the area under a time-velocity graph, Science, 351, 482-484', 'http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.aad8085', 'side Y 4''-5''', 972, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (397, 'ⲁϥⳓⲱⲡⲉ ⳋⲣⲡⳉⲱⲧ ⲻⲥⲟⲩⲛⳗⲁⳗⲉ ⲛ ⲡϥⲟⲟⲩ ⲻⲙⲓⲥⲧϥ ...', 'afšôpe šrpxôt – counčače n pfoou – mistf ...', 371, 'If Jupiter was a hostile star on his his day of birth ...', 'P.Lond. 98', 'horoscope', 'Egypt', '95', 'J. Černý, P.E. Kahle, and R.A. Parker, 1957, The Old Coptic Horoscope, Journal of Egyptian Archaeology 43, 86-100.', '', '127', 505, '98', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1949, 'TIR.AN ina KUR GIB', '', 1734, 'A rainbow stretched in the east.', 'BM 36729 (ADRT I No. -343)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '-343 (Artaxerxes III year 15)', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', 'http://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/adsd/adart1/corpus', 'rev. 17''', 2038, '156', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (738, '', 'ḥn=f n=w ḏd gšp r tꜣ p.t ỉ.nw r pꜣ ỉtm m-ỉr dỉ.t ḥp md.t ỉw=s ḫpr [... | ...] nꜣ rmṯ.w ꜥš=w nꜣy=w sẖꜣ.w gšp=w r tꜣ p.t nw=w r pꜣ ỉtm ỉ.ỉr=w gm pꜣ syw n wsỉr r ḫꜣꜥ=f tꜣy=f mỉ.t ...', 661, 'He ordered them: "Observe the sky and look at the disc. Do not allow that matters are hidden ... [... | ...] the people. They read their scriptures, they observed the sky, and they looked at the disc. They found that the Star of Osiris, in that it had left its path ..."', 'P.Carlsberg XI 5', 'literary text', 'Tebtunis', '1st - 2nd cent. CE', 'Quack, J. F., 2019, Isis, Thot und Arian aud der Suche nach Osiris, in J. F. Quack and K. Ryholt, eds.,  Demotic Literary Texts from Tebtunis and Beyond, Copenhagen 2019, 77-138.', '', 'x+22-x+23', 854, '80-81', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1210, '(22) ina 5 DANNA si-man 5 UŠ
(23) ᵈsin ana ᵈUTU.ŠU₂.A tu-šaḫ-ḫa-az', '', 1085, '(22) In 5 bēru time (23) you let Sin proceed 5 UŠ to the west.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. ii 22-23', 1303, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1968, '', 'ỉw=w ḏd n=k [fy 15 2/3 r 100] | ỉw=k šꜥṱ 6 ẖ[n 100 sp 94] | iw=k ḏd ḫr-š[m 6 r 94 r1]5 2/3 | my ỉn=f 1/3 r 47', 1755, 'If it is said to you [carry 15 2/3 to 100,] | you subtract 6 from [100, 94 remains]. | You shall say [6] goes to 94 with the result 1]5 2/3 | Cause it to be brought to 1/3 result 47.', 'P.Cairo J.E. 89127', 'mathematical text', 'Tuna el-Gebel', '3rd cent. BCE', 'R.A. Parker, 1972, Demotic Mathematical Texts, Brown Egyptological Studies 7, Providence RI/London.', '', '1-4', 2058, '37', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1192, 'ὡρασκόπος Λέοντι μυρ(ῶν) ιγ οἴκου ⟨Ἡ⟩λίου ὁρίοις {θ} Κρόνου διμ(ερισμῶν) β', '', 1075, 'Ascendant in Leo, 13 degrees, house of the Sun, terms of Saturn, decan 2', 'PSI I 23a', 'horoscope', 'Antinoopolis', '338 CE', '(GH 338)', '', '', 1286, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2168, 'Et hoc tamen et illud sidus eiusdem condicionis est, cum effectu et natura dissimile sit. Intra brevissimum tempus Aries extollitur, Libra tardissime emergit;', '', 1920, 'Yet both constellations are of the same class even though they are unlike in influence and characteristics. Aries rises within a very short time, Libra emerges quite slowly;', 'Seneca, Natural Questions', 'philosophy', '', '62/63 CE', 'Seneca. Natural Questions, Volume II: Books 4-7. Translated by Thomas H. Corcoran. Loeb Classical Library 457. Cambridge, MA: Harvard University Press, 1972.', 'https://www.loebclassics.com/view/seneca_younger-natural_questions/1971/pb_LCL457.283.xml', '7.27.3', 2248, '282-283', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (944, 'Solis [...] annuique reditus', '', 830, 'the yearly return of the sun', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '1.0.5', 1032, '1.2', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (332, '', 'pꜣ ꜥ.wy n | ḥr-pꜣ-kꜣ pꜣ-ḥr-ꜥnḫ pꜣ mw', 318, 'The house(s) of | Saturn: Capricorn and Aquarius', 'P.Carlsberg 81', 'astrological treatise', 'Tebtunis', '2nd cent. CE', '', '', '', 426, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1061, 'Stellae quinque, id est Saturnus, Iuppiter, Mars, Venus, Mercurius, matutinae sunt aut vespertinae aut occiduales aut absconsae, quae a Graecis afaneis et synodicae dicuntur, aut acronyctae.', '', 951, 'The five planets, that is, Saturn, Jupiter, Mars, Venus, Mercury, are either matutine, vespertine, setting, or hidden (by the Sun''s rays). These the Greeks call afaneis (hidden), synodicae (in conjunction with he sun), or acronyctae (at nightfall).', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.8.1', 1155, '1.50', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1256, '[ina] ⸢6.42⸣ ME.MEŠ TA IGI ana IGI 30 KI DU', '', 1119, 'In 6,42 days from appearance to appearance the position (of Jupiter) goes forward by 30.', 'BM 34081+ (BMAPT No. 18)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 250-50 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2016, Ancient Babylonian astronomers calculated Jupiters position from the area under a time-velocity graph, Science, 351, 482-484', 'http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.aad8085', 'obv. i 5', 1349, '482-484', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1035, 'In altitudinibus itaque suis gaudent[es] constitutae', '', 926, 'When planets are in their own exaltations we say that they rejoice', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965193/html', '2.3.2', 1130, '1.43', '');
