(7) 1.58.31.6.40 LA₂-u₂ 4.46.42.⸢57⸣.46.40 GAR-an ša₂ al-la 1.58.31.⸢6⸣.[40]
(8) LA₂-u₂ LA₂-u₂ EN 1.58.13.20 ma-ṭu-u₂ A.RA₂ 8.20 DU KI 4.46.42.57.4⸢6.40⸣
( 9) TAB-ma GAR-an', '', 1308, '(6) [Opposite] (7) 1,58;31,6,40, decreasing, you put 4,46;42,57,46,40. Whatever (the amount) by which it is less than 1,58;31,6, [40], (8) decreasing, until 1,58;13,20, decreasing, you multiply by 8;20, add with 4,46;42,57,46,40, and (9) put down.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. i 6-9', 1569, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1672, 'In Librae parte XV. oritur Haedus.', '', 1464, 'At 15° Libra rises the Young Goat.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '8.12.3', 1757, '2.306', '');
