(8) 1 ⸢KUŠ₃ ana NIM⸣ DIB', '', 1704, '(7) Night of (day) 13, ME (= moonrise to sunset) was 11 (UŠ), measured (despite) clouds; beginning of the night, Sin was 20 fingers above the twins’ star of the shepherd, Sin (8)  having passed 1 cubit to the east.', 'BM 46229 (ADRT I No. -346)', 'astronomical diary', 'Babylon', '347 BCE', 'Sachs, A. J., Hunger, H. 1988. Astronomical Diaries and Related Texts from Babylonia, Vol. I: Diaries from 652 B.C. to 262 B.C. Vienna: Verlag der Österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften.', 'http://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/adsd/adart1/sig?☣%40adsd%2Fadart1%25akk%3ATUR₃%3Dtarbaṣu%5Bpen%2F%2Fhalo%5DN´N%24tarbaṣa', 'obv. 7-8', 1996, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1403, 'Sed et in Pisces et in Geminos cum circumiens venerit, haec eadem decernit quae in tropicis.', '', 1252, 'But when he—going around—enters Pisces and Gemini, he indicates the same things as he did in the tropical signs.', 'Firmicus Maternus, Mathesis', 'astrological compendium', 'Sicily', 'ca. 334 CE', 'Firmicus Maternus. 1897. Ivlii Firmici Materni Matheseos Libri VIII, ed. W. Kroll, F. Skutsch. Stuttgart: B. G. Teubner.', 'https://www.degruyter.com/document/doi/10.1515/9783110965186/html', '5.3.20', 1495, '2.35', '');
