INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (1427, '(36) 6 DANNA LA₂ ša₂ ME ⸢ša₂⸣ ITI.ŠE U₄.28.KAM 3 6 DANNA ina 4.30 9 DANNA
(37) E₁₁ 1.30 ana KUR šamaš₂ re-ḫi 1.30 ina 6 12 DANNA E₁₁-ma 4.30 IB₂.TAG₄
(38) U₄.28.KAM 4.30 ⸢ME⸣ NIM.A ana KUR E.A GAR-an', '', 1267, '(36) The length of daylight for the 28th of month XII is 6 beru. You deduct 3,0 (UŠ i.e.) 6 bēru, from 4,30 (UŠ , i.e.) 9 bēru , (37) 1,30 (UŠ) until sunrise remains. You deduct 1,30 (UŠ) from 6,0 (UŠ, i.e.) 12 bēru, 4,30 is the remainder (38) for day 28. You put down 4,30 (UŠ) as the time (from New Moon) to sunrise in order to predict KUR.', 'BM 32167+ (BMAPT No. 53)', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon', 'ca. 350-250 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2012. Babylonian Mathematical Astronomy: Procedure Texts. New York: Springer.', '', 'rev. ii 35-38', 1513, '', '');
