(11'') TA 2.24 ZI-ma', '', 1088, '(7'') You place the “crossing” in its path, in its middle. [The day when] (8'') it passes the “crossing”, you see how long it is tak[ing ...?] (9'') (Concerning) this 10;45, you see when it is halved: (0);12, the [large] width, [you multiply by (0);12, it is] (10'') (0);2,24. (0);9,30, the “pinched” width, [you multiply] by (0);9,30, [it is (0);1,30,15.] (11'') You subtract it from (0);2,24.', 'BM 34757', 'mathematical astronomy: procedure text', 'Babylon?', 'ca. 350-100 BCE', 'Ossendrijver, M. 2016, Ancient Babylonian astronomers calculated Jupiters position from the area under a time-velocity graph, Science, 351, 482-484', 'http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.aad8085', 'side Y 7''-11''', 1307, '', '');
INSERT INTO public.quotations VALUES (2372, '', 'sr pr(.t) Spd.t m tp(y)-rnp.t mꜣꜣ=f s m hrw hb=s tpy ỉp m nmt.t=s r tr.w n dhn ỉm mꜣꜣ ỉr(t)=s nb(t) rꜥ nb sr.n=s  nb m-ꜥ=f', 2074, 'The one who foretells the coming forth (heliacal rising) of Sothis, who observes her in the day of her first feast, who establishes her striding in the times of touching ground (?) who observes  all her doings every day. All that she has foretold is in his command.', 'JE 38545', 'autobiographical inscription', 'Egypt', '330-30 BCE', 'Altmann-Wendling, Victoria and Marco Stockhusen 2020. Die Statue eines ägyptische Priesters und Astronomen (JE 38545). In Färber, Roland and Rita Gautschy (eds), Zeit in den Kulturen des Altertums: antike Chronologie im Spiegel der Quellen, 103-115. Wien; Köln; Weimar: Böhlau', '', '2', 2434, '', '');
